1
00:00:10,427 --> 00:00:11,261
KARAOKE

2
00:00:11,344 --> 00:00:14,347
- Ugh, seriously.
- How was your date?

3
00:00:14,431 --> 00:00:16,433
Who went on a date
with Hyuk-joon and Jin-woo?

4
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:17,892
- I did.
- Wow.

5
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:20,145
- I asked them…
- Your dates overlapped?

6
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:23,314
I asked them if they had been on
the same date before, and they said yes.

7
00:00:23,398 --> 00:00:27,569
So, I was feeling awkward because
I really didn't have anything to say.

8
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:29,112
It wasn't bad or anything,

9
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:34,034
but I imagine that all three of us
looked very uncomfortable on that date.

10
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:35,785
- I know…
- Why were the guys bothered?

11
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:38,496
Exactly. Why?
We were the ones who asked questions.

12
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,124
Wait, hold on. If anyone
should be upset, it's Jae-seo.

13
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:42,417
That's right.

14
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,586
Honestly, Jae-seo should be
the most bothered by it.

15
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:47,672
I'm really… I'm really worried
that Jae-seo might leave the show.

16
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:52,010
I know, because if I were in his shoes,
I'd be crying in my room, for real.

17
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:54,179
Seriously, that would really fucking hurt.

18
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,722
Han-ju, behave!

19
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:58,349
- She's right, though.
- She's showing concern for him.

20
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:03,229
For me, I feel like my date today
was just a net loss.

21
00:01:03,313 --> 00:01:06,191
But when it comes to you, it's so obvious,

22
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,652
and everyone must kind of know.

23
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:10,779
Who I like? Me?

24
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,074
Jae-seo knows for sure,
but I'm guessing all the others also know.

25
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:15,158
I think they do. Uh-huh.

26
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:17,535
- Does it show that much?
- Mmm.

27
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:18,745
- Really?
- Yeah.

28
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:23,249
Other than what we've actually revealed,
you mean you can tell from my actions?

29
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,126
Mm-hmm.

30
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:28,421
So today, after seeing the tumbler,
I thought, "So it's mutual?"

31
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:29,881
- Right?
- Me too.

32
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:33,927
I don't think he even noticed it,
though. He was too sick.

33
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:35,470
Oh, then it's an opportunity.

34
00:01:35,553 --> 00:01:38,348
- He's been lying down in the dorm all day.
- Back from the hospital?

35
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:41,184
Only coming out for the date,
and then going back to the dorm.

36
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:44,270
I'm doing whatever I can
to show my affection for him, but…

37
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:47,065
Previously, we used to make
a lot of eye contact,

38
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:49,442
but after coming back from today's dates,

39
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:51,444
he didn't even make
eye contact with me at all.

40
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:53,655
Yeah, this usually tends
to bother women a lot.

41
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:54,989
It really does.

42
00:01:55,073 --> 00:01:57,951
He kept looking away like this,
so I thought…

43
00:01:58,034 --> 00:01:59,035
"Hmm."

44
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:02,247
"Did he get a bad injection?"

45
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:06,668
- Did something go wrong?
- It was sudden, to be fair.

46
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:09,212
I was also kind of like,
"Well, this is nice," "What's this?"

47
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,673
"Oh, this is nice," "What's this?"
"This is nice," "What's this?"

48
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,633
That's exactly how it plays out.

49
00:02:13,716 --> 00:02:15,593
- It's not easy.
- No, it's not.

50
00:02:15,677 --> 00:02:18,471
Hey, want to go for a walk?
The weather's nice.

51
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:19,556
Let's just go.

52
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:21,724
- I guess everyone's feeling troubled.
- I know.

53
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:24,519
I feel like I might have
taken the wrong stance.

54
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:26,020
- Why's that?
- The thing is…

55
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:30,108
I kept going on dates
exclusively with Hyuk-joon,

56
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:33,236
and I know that we're both
attracted to each other.

57
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:35,238
But on the other hand,

58
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:42,078
I felt that he might lose interest in me
if I were too quick to…

59
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,079
- Give away…
- Yes.

60
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,622
- Uh-huh.
- Give away my heart.

61
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:52,046
So for this date, I was kind of thinking,
"Should I try to make him jealous?"

62
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,799
But really, I mean,
make him jealous, my ass.

63
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:57,302
What do I know about
making someone jealous?

64
00:02:57,385 --> 00:03:00,180
I probably just come across as a weirdo.

65
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:04,726
Ah, I went with a terrible plan.

66
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:05,977
That's kind of cute.

67
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,646
- Oh, gosh!
- Oh, that is adorable.

68
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:09,856
So I…

69
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:13,234
Mine was with Jin-woo and Seung-hyun.

70
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:17,322
And Jin-woo said he had whittled down
his options to three people,

71
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:19,407
so I thought, "Oh, really?"

72
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:22,744
But when I combined that with the contents
of the 5 Minute Library,

73
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:26,164
I got the feeling that I wasn't one
of those three people.

74
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:28,625
The Library… don't worry about it.

75
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:31,044
- It's not absolute.
- Of course, it's not.

76
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:35,548
But he also said that the main points
he wrote in the Library

77
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:38,927
wouldn't change significantly,
but the little things could change.

78
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,553
- Of course.
- I guess that makes sense.

79
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,597
For me too, what's going on
with Hyuk-joon right now

80
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,307
is different from what I wrote
in my diary.

81
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:45,433
I know. Me too.

82
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:47,477
I was like, "How do they expect me
to write this

83
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,229
when I've never been in a relationship?"

84
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:51,397
- When we've never even dated a man?
- Uh-huh.

85
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:54,025
Like, "Do you prefer indoor dates
or outdoor dates?"

86
00:03:54,108 --> 00:03:56,527
How would I know when I've never tried it?

87
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:58,613
The only place I've been to with a guy
is a gaming cafe.

88
00:03:58,696 --> 00:04:00,865
The only thing I've done with a guy
is a group project.

89
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:02,700
I swear.

90
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:07,914
I just asked ChatGPT about the things
I've never considered before.

91
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,750
"ChatGPT."

92
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:13,002
GPT can sometimes gives you
the wrong information, though.

93
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:15,546
- This conversation's really fun.
- They're adorable.

94
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,382
We're such eternal singles.

95
00:04:17,465 --> 00:04:19,592
Oh, we're in trouble
if we have to ask ChatGPT

96
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:21,886
for things that we'd never
thought about before.

97
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,680
That's right.

98
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:27,016
So I thought about it for a while,
then I told him about my feelings for him.

99
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:30,937
But ever since we got back,
he doesn't look me in the eye.

100
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:32,563
Jin-woo?

101
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:35,608
Or maybe he feels uncomfortable
because a girl he's not interested in

102
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:37,443
suddenly expressed her interest in him.

103
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,611
Oh…

104
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:41,030
- I--
- It can't be helped.

105
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:42,407
They have to endure it.

106
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:45,618
- That's right. Endure it. Endure it.
- Endure it!

107
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:48,955
Hey, telling you that
took a lot of courage, so endure it.

108
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,790
That's right.
This is just the way we flirt.

109
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:52,542
That's right. We flirt with courage.

110
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:59,924
So I was a little upset
because of that. Upset.

111
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,301
I feel conflicted.

112
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:06,973
I think that before coming here,
I was really confident, thinking,

113
00:05:07,056 --> 00:05:10,518
"I'll express my feelings,
and try out everything,"

114
00:05:10,601 --> 00:05:12,020
but now that I'm here…

115
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:16,649
I made a decision
about my first impression vote.

116
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,235
I decided on Ahn Seung-hyun, but…

117
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,112
…that happened,
and then you guys just left.

118
00:05:21,195 --> 00:05:23,156
Left for what? I didn't get that?

119
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:26,075
- That conversation did not flow.
- It's so frustrating to watch.

120
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,911
Ah, right. I think Hyuk-joon is my…

121
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:30,496
Yes, he's my current top pick.

122
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:33,166
- Ah! Ouch!
- He went too hard on her.

123
00:05:33,249 --> 00:05:34,709
HER TOP PICK
WOULDN'T STOP SHOOTING HER

124
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:37,128
My second pick was Jae-seo.

125
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:39,422
- He also went on a date with her.
- Because seriously…

126
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:41,507
- He had broken a chair.
- Ah…

127
00:05:41,591 --> 00:05:44,552
First off, my top pick is Jin-woo today.

128
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,263
By the way, I looked at your diary.

129
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:49,932
- You checked out mine?
- Uh-huh. I was looking through it, and…

130
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:52,643
I chose you as my top pick
and you as my second pick.

131
00:05:52,727 --> 00:05:54,562
- Really?
- So that's why we're here.

132
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:56,647
This isn't easy.
It's not working out for her.

133
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:58,149
He's avoiding eye contact.

134
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,360
Oh, man…

135
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:04,530
Seriously, I don't know if I'm slow
on the uptake, like seriously slow,

136
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:07,033
but I was really totally clueless.

137
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:08,785
So, you know…

138
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:11,454
Well, I'm just not feeling it at all.

139
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:15,541
It must feel like
nothing's working out for her at all.

140
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:18,586
Can I come over once in a while?

141
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:19,670
- Come where?
- To you.

142
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:20,755
Uh-huh.

143
00:06:21,422 --> 00:06:23,716
You can come over too,
if you feel frustrated.

144
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,718
I'll go to him
and give him a piece of my mind.

145
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:28,596
"You'd better tread lightly, mister."

146
00:06:28,679 --> 00:06:29,972
"You, come outside."

147
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:32,683
- "If you don't, I'll tear you to shreds."
- To shreds.

148
00:06:33,434 --> 00:06:35,770
- Try talking to him later.
- Mm-hmm, I should do that.

149
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:40,108
Well, since none of the men are doing it,
what else can the women do but step up?

150
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:42,652
- Oh, I love that mindset.
- Yes, good. A strong mind.

151
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:46,781
Man, why does it feel like a battle
of the sexes suddenly broke out today?

152
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:47,740
Mm-hmm.

153
00:06:47,824 --> 00:06:50,493
Did you guys also talk about
how many dates you've been on and stuff?

154
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:51,494
Kind of.

155
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:53,329
Haven't you been on at least two?

156
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:55,540
- Well, two.
- Well, I…

157
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:57,667
What's with that smirk?

158
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,127
- Seriously.
- What on earth?

159
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:01,879
That was the kind of smirk
you only see on super popular men.

160
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:03,131
Hey, listen up, you punks.

161
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:04,715
Wow!

162
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,843
- What's that, punk?
- That was too much.

163
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,719
You guys seem to be getting
the wrong idea.

164
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:11,472
- Wow.
- So let me tell you how wrong you are.

165
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,641
I got "I'm not like you guys"
vibes from him.

166
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:14,725
You're gonna get it.

167
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:17,186
- Haven't you been on at least two?
- Mm-hmm, well, two.

168
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:22,150
Hyuk-joon and I went on the same date
twice in a row.

169
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,110
- Oh, really?
- Uh-huh.

170
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:28,239
He was approaching from afar, with…
how should I say this? A radiant smile.

171
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:30,741
Well, dude, I mean… I just, I thought…

172
00:07:32,201 --> 00:07:33,202
you were so cool.

173
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,912
<i>- Hyung, </i>you know you look good.
- Wow.

174
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,957
To be honest,
you look like a pretty boy, okay?

175
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,626
You look like an idol, with that
tiny face of yours and everything.

176
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:42,128
You look like a pretty boy.

177
00:07:42,211 --> 00:07:44,088
- Complimenting each other again.
- Right.

178
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:46,924
Man, I'm so sick and tired of this.

179
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:48,968
What's going on? Can we come in?

180
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:51,679
- Did you come to get something?
- No.

181
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:54,557
I need to make some soju bombs.

182
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,225
Everyone's jonesing for a drink.

183
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,728
No one's had any drinks yet,
but looks like all bets are off.

184
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:00,771
- What? Whoa!
- They didn't tell me either.

185
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:03,107
- Wow.
- Fill us in on it later.

186
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:05,610
- Wow, pouring soju into a can of beer.
- Ah…

187
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:14,202
Hmm? What are you up to?

188
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:15,745
I was going to drink some warm water.

189
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:17,663
- Are you feeling okay?
- Uh-huh, I'm fine.

190
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,500
Are you having a chat with the girls?

191
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:22,418
- We already had a chat.
- You did?

192
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,962
I calmed my troubled mind
before coming here.

193
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,464
- You were troubled?
- Uh-huh.

194
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:27,381
Why's that?

195
00:08:27,465 --> 00:08:29,383
I felt so uncomfortable during our date.

196
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:35,139
Do you know what kind of date it was?
That date? Why there were two of you?

197
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,141
- Oh, I know that.
- How did you know?

198
00:08:39,477 --> 00:08:41,938
- Do you want to take this over there?
- Okay. Uh-huh, mm-hmm.

199
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:42,897
Uh-huh, right.

200
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:45,483
Yes. I think they could use
a private conversation.

201
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:47,902
So you knew what kind of date it was.

202
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,612
Uh-huh, so I…

203
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:53,491
You might have heard
who I went on a date with today.

204
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:54,617
Uh-huh.

205
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,827
- But Su… Su-ji was there.
- Uh-huh.

206
00:08:56,911 --> 00:09:00,915
I hadn't even considered
that possibility, so…

207
00:09:00,998 --> 00:09:03,000
Su-ji? I didn't know about Su-ji.

208
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:05,753
What? You said you knew all about it.

209
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:08,130
- No. Su-ji wasn't around when we talked.
- Oh, really?

210
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:09,340
I couldn't have anticipated.

211
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,385
Oh…

212
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:15,012
You're quite the popular guy, aren't you?

213
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:17,265
You sure went on a lot of dates today.

214
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:23,145
Don't you think saying that
in such a calm tone

215
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,855
would maybe freak me out?

216
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:28,985
I think Hyuk-joon might be liking this.

217
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:31,487
It feels as though
she seems to care about him.

218
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:35,866
To be honest, I picked Seung-hyun
in the first impression vote.

219
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:37,285
- I see, okay.
- Yeah.

220
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:41,706
And back then, you were my second pick.

221
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:42,999
- Oh?
- Uh-huh.

222
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:49,088
But then, after the first day interview,
we came to the lounge and talked, and…

223
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:50,923
I like women who are into anime.

224
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:52,800
Ah, are you into anime?

225
00:09:52,883 --> 00:09:54,051
Yes, I'm really into anime.

226
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:56,679
Partaking in a common hobby
is a good thing, so…

227
00:09:57,763 --> 00:10:00,808
I thought, "We might click
really well hobby-wise."

228
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:02,101
So after that…

229
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:07,148
I started to notice
I felt very attracted to you.

230
00:10:07,231 --> 00:10:08,899
Oh, she's expressing herself. That's it.

231
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:10,359
She's being very straightforward now.

232
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:12,737
Oh, I'd been meaning to ask you this.

233
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:16,574
- You're older than me by four years.
- Yes, yes.

234
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:20,453
Would you rather I kept addressing you
as "you" as I do now,

235
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:22,913
or would you prefer
I addressed you more respectfully?

236
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:27,543
Well, I don't want us to put
too many restrictions on that.

237
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:31,172
I'll talk more respectfully from now on.

238
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:33,007
Very well.

239
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:34,133
But…

240
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:38,220
if I actually do that,
would you be okay with it?

241
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:43,726
Maybe I should just keep saying "you"--

242
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:45,519
- Are you really asking?
- Huh?

243
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:46,604
Oh, nothing, nothing.

244
00:10:47,229 --> 00:10:48,606
More respectfully, then.

245
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:54,528
She showed interest for me. Just me.

246
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,572
"Just." "Just me."

247
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:59,325
Hyun-seo's been expressing
her feelings for me…

248
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,036
more often now,

249
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:06,082
and I think that's definitely
a pretty big sign.

250
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:09,877
I finally felt like I had become
someone special to her,

251
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,296
and I must admit I felt good about it.

252
00:11:13,464 --> 00:11:14,715
So he did notice, good.

253
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:17,218
I guess Hyuk-joon
was just craving some affection.

254
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:19,261
Earlier on, she asked him,
"Are you feeling okay?"

255
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:20,763
That's when he let go of his resentment.

256
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:23,265
Even before the conversation,
it must've helped letting go.

257
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:26,352
So before, was he just acting out
to get her attention?

258
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:27,478
He was just sulking.

259
00:11:27,561 --> 00:11:29,480
Mm-hmm. He was sulking
and wanted her to know.

260
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:33,067
I'm really curious as to the reason
why you're an eternal single.

261
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:36,445
Oh, well, I'm often told
I'm a cold person.

262
00:11:37,321 --> 00:11:38,698
I wouldn't say you're cold…

263
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:44,495
but you do know you have to be cold
to the other girls, right?

264
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:50,167
They're basically giving off couple vibes.

265
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:53,421
Sometimes you say things
that gives me chills, you know.

266
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,005
You're not wrong.

267
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:57,758
You could see it as a warning.
You should tread lightly, then.

268
00:11:58,759 --> 00:12:01,762
If you use your secret weapon
while you're on a date with another woman,

269
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:07,059
your clothes will get torn to shreds,
right then and there.

270
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,520
- Ah, right, right, right.
- She's bringing that up again.

271
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:11,605
She should tear his clothes to shreds
before throwing him out.

272
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:14,942
- Mentioned tearing up his clothes twice.
- Man, she's crushing it right now.

273
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:19,238
Thanks to the power of alcohol,
I managed to get this out.

274
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:21,741
Alcohol? Did you drink a lot?

275
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,076
I poured soju in my beer.

276
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,244
- For real?
- Uh-huh.

277
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:29,582
Although you couldn't drink
anything else than warm water.

278
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:32,918
Oh, my God, those eyes.

279
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:34,962
She was trying to act
a little cute just now.

280
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,630
She looked like Puss in Boots.

281
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,258
- Bring me booze.
- Han-ju, don't!

282
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:41,552
- She's good at mixing drinks.
- Looks good.

283
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:43,471
Han-ju is good at mixing drinks.

284
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:46,891
- They're drinking a lot.
- It's perfect.

285
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:48,017
Is it good?

286
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,686
It doesn't have the foul taste
of Chamisul.

287
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:52,396
- Surprisingly--
- What's wrong?

288
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:55,441
- How do you drink this? Seriously.
- I think it's great.

289
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:57,193
I'm just used to it.

290
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:58,944
- Oh, boy, Han-ju.
- Oh, no.

291
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,489
I must admit,
I'm feeling a little troubled,

292
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:03,532
so I'm definitely
gonna need a drink tonight.

293
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,659
- Good job today, everyone.
- Cheers.

294
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:12,875
When she gets drunk,
Han-ju can get a little…

295
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:14,710
No way. It can't be.

296
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:16,712
Why are you drinking alone?

297
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:19,256
That's right.
Tonight, I have drinking buddies.

298
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:31,769
- Huh?
- Oh, no. She's drunk.

299
00:13:31,852 --> 00:13:33,813
- Here it comes.
- She's about to keel over.

300
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:36,607
Han-ju, think of your past,
think of all those blind dates you ruined

301
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:38,275
because of your drunken outbursts.

302
00:13:39,276 --> 00:13:40,528
Maybe you should take it slow.

303
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:44,490
Such a shame. This is a once…
uh, once-in-ten-days opportunity.

304
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:46,575
Yes!

305
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:50,037
Just--

306
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,248
Oh, sorry, sorry, sorry.

307
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:54,333
The glass tipping is definitely a sign.

308
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:57,336
Now, the only thing that can unfold
in this situation is an altercation.

309
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:59,505
- Let's go.
- Yes, ah, yes, yes.

310
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:01,715
What? We should empty
all of these and go again.

311
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:03,300
We'll drink with you again tomorrow.

312
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,970
- No, but seriously…
- Don't "but seriously" us.

313
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:08,305
I know this is a classic
drunk person line,

314
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:10,391
but I'm not even a little bit drunk.

315
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:13,519
No, you know that's not true.
Let's drink tomorrow.

316
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:16,272
Yeah, that's right.
We should clean this up.

317
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:18,232
I… I'm gonna need a written oath.

318
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:19,316
Huh?

319
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,569
Because these guys
aren't drinkers usually,

320
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:22,987
she's having so much fun today.

321
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:24,196
We could just make a recording.

322
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,948
Okay. Then let's clean up.

323
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,742
- Good night.
- See you tomorrow.

324
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:31,161
- See you tomorrow.
- Oh, thank goodness.

325
00:14:31,245 --> 00:14:33,247
Han-ju is in for hangover soup
in the morning.

326
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:36,125
Such a relief. Still, it's a good thing
they got to talk.

327
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:39,628
Right? I mean, after the three-way date,
she became a different person.

328
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:42,047
Hyun-seo properly
expressed her feelings to Hyuk-joon,

329
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:45,384
and I felt that Hyuk-joon
had let go of his resentment

330
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:47,386
to a very large extent.

331
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:50,431
It definitely felt like the grudge he held
against her had somewhat gone away.

332
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:51,473
I could tell.

333
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:54,018
I think she felt it necessary
to try and play hard to get,

334
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:57,021
but as expected, playing hard to get
is a luxury for eternal singles.

335
00:14:57,104 --> 00:14:58,147
Right.

336
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:06,947
Man, our room is a mess right now.

337
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,074
Oh, really? Do you think…

338
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:12,286
- Oh, no, what is it? Are you okay?
- Uh-huh.

339
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:15,497
When you drink too much,
you should deal with the consequences.

340
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:21,921
In this room are Su-ji's current
and former love interests,

341
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:23,047
if you know what I mean.

342
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,424
Ah…

343
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:30,471
Are you a bit better?

344
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:31,722
Oh, really? That's good.

345
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:33,849
I got it all out of my system.

346
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,809
- Go and sleep, please.
- Huh?

347
00:15:35,893 --> 00:15:38,729
No, seriously, I'm all better now,
seriously.

348
00:15:38,812 --> 00:15:40,272
- You're completely fine?
- Really?

349
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:42,566
- Uh-huh.
- The double-0 went wild today.

350
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:45,069
The double-0s went on an absolute bender.

351
00:15:45,152 --> 00:15:47,571
Which other double-0 drank with you?
Did you drink?

352
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:49,490
- Oh, yeah.
- Oh, this is fun.

353
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,116
You wrote a letter or something?

354
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,160
- I wrote a letter.
- Oh, you wrote a letter?

355
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,120
1 HOUR AGO

356
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:58,415
When I opened the mailbox,
I was surprised because I actually found

357
00:15:58,499 --> 00:15:59,917
another letter in there.

358
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,294
So I thought,
"Oh, it's… it's a competition."

359
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,341
- Was it yours?
- Huh?

360
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:10,094
Was there a gift in there as well?

361
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,556
That was indeed mine.

362
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:16,558
Yeah, I saw it.

363
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:19,144
2 HOURS AGO

364
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,105
When everyone was drinking in the lounge,

365
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:23,649
I went to my room alone
and wrote a letter to Su-ji.

366
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:25,693
She was my top pick all along,

367
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:27,736
but I never got a chance
to go on a date with her

368
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,363
or spend time with her,

369
00:16:29,446 --> 00:16:31,240
so I just wrote her a letter saying,

370
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:33,325
"I'd like to talk,
this is how I feel about you,"

371
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:34,868
and put a gift in there as well.

372
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:37,037
Has Jin-woo ever expressed
his feelings to Su-ji?

373
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,580
- I don't think so.
- Not properly.

374
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:40,249
So Su-ji doesn't know yet.

375
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:42,292
She said she'd lost
the black leather gloves

376
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:43,502
she wore here on the first day,

377
00:16:43,585 --> 00:16:46,839
and there was a similar pair,
so I brought them for her.

378
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:51,885
- Well, that complicates things.
- Complicates things how?

379
00:16:51,969 --> 00:16:53,971
Huh? Because there's an overlap.

380
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:55,723
Ugh, how does that matter?

381
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:58,559
Well, I simply told her how I feel,
and it's up to her to decide.

382
00:16:58,642 --> 00:17:00,394
Right.

383
00:17:00,477 --> 00:17:02,771
So, who's everyone's top pick, then?

384
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:06,066
The two of us got to meet up,
but you two didn't talk yet.

385
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,235
- The three of us overlap.
- Really?

386
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:10,320
- It's Su-ji, isn't it?
- Right.

387
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:11,447
Right, ah…

388
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,616
- Well, Su-ji--
- Want me to be honest? She's hella hot.

389
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:16,785
- That's how I see her.
- That's true.

390
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:18,704
Want me to tell you something else?

391
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:21,665
I was a little jealous when you two
went out to talk earlier.

392
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:25,169
- Oh…
- But it wasn't exactly…

393
00:17:25,252 --> 00:17:26,837
It wasn't that kind of conversation?

394
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:29,840
No, it wasn't. It was more like,
we were clarifying some things.

395
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:32,676
So what? The two of you
still went out together.

396
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,136
You guys also went out earlier.

397
00:17:34,219 --> 00:17:36,472
What's with this sudden need
to escalate things?

398
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:39,516
He's using liquid courage
to say everything he's wanted to say.

399
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:42,394
- Is he out of his mind?
- I'm drunk. Cut me some slack.

400
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:44,188
- You're all sobered up now.
- Yeah, that's true.

401
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:47,483
Man, it's a good thing
I got off that train a day earlier, jeez.

402
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:50,194
Seeing all of them suffer…

403
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:53,822
I know I shouldn't have,
but I found it kind of hilarious.

404
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:57,576
It felt like I was definitely
in the driver's seat for a moment.

405
00:17:58,243 --> 00:17:59,369
It's a heated night.

406
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:01,246
We're in for an eventful day tomorrow.

407
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,998
Might be determined by fate.

408
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,293
The weather's nice.

409
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:09,463
- You hungry?
- I want a blueberry smoothie.

410
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:12,132
- A blueberry smoothie?
- Blueberry smoothie.

411
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:16,637
We should make a lot
so there's enough for everyone.

412
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:18,806
Lots of mouths to feed.

413
00:18:19,389 --> 00:18:20,390
Ooh, ooh.

414
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:23,393
- You want some?
- Mm-hmm, I sure do.

415
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:26,605
In that case, one, two, three, four…

416
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:29,733
Since Soo-hyun said she wanted some,
we should make some for her.

417
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:31,568
- Huh?
- Soo-hyun?

418
00:18:32,152 --> 00:18:36,156
Yesterday, I gave her a blueberry
smoothie, and so I already knew.

419
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,241
LAST NIGHT

420
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:38,909
I'm about to have this.
Would you like some?

421
00:18:38,992 --> 00:18:39,910
Huh, what is it?

422
00:18:39,993 --> 00:18:42,162
- It's milk and blueberries
- Uh-huh.

423
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:44,456
With strawberries blended together.

424
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:45,916
- Ooh, I'd like that.
- Sure.

425
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:48,043
- Look at that.
- They spent time together?

426
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:49,044
That's nice.

427
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:52,798
This sure is delicious.
Could you make some for me next time?

428
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:57,427
Where are you from again?

429
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:59,638
I'm from Daejeon, in Chungcheong-do.

430
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:00,722
Oh, yes, Sungsimdang.

431
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:02,224
- You watch baseball?
- I do, yes.

432
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:07,396
We happened to get
into another conversation that day,

433
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:09,565
and it really seemed we got along well.

434
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:12,359
I remembered Soo-hyun
loving the blueberry smoothie

435
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:13,986
and wanting to try it again.

436
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:17,489
So he remembered.
Mmm, what a thoughtful man, Tae-hoon.

437
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:19,658
To show
that I was somewhat attracted to her,

438
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:20,993
I stored it in the fridge.

439
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,244
He's attracted to her?

440
00:19:22,327 --> 00:19:24,955
He's discovering Soo-hyun's charm.

441
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:27,916
And to be honest,
Su-ji wasn't responding to me at all,

442
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:32,546
so I thought I probably
wasn't on her list of favorites.

443
00:19:32,629 --> 00:19:37,384
That's why I thought, "Maybe I should
let go of my feelings for Su-ji."

444
00:19:41,805 --> 00:19:43,098
Oh! Hi!

445
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:46,018
I put yours in the fridge.

446
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:47,853
- What?
- You should have it. The smoothie.

447
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:49,897
Ooh, thanks!

448
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,356
Oh, of course she's touched.

449
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:52,858
Oh, he's so thoughtful.

450
00:19:52,941 --> 00:19:54,109
I like what I see.

451
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,528
- Are they looking good?
- Yeah. A college couple, that's good.

452
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:57,613
Oh, you're right.

453
00:19:57,696 --> 00:19:59,323
- It's so cold in here.
- Did you--

454
00:19:59,406 --> 00:20:01,116
Seo-yoon, can we talk?

455
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,911
What's this? Oh, she's being summoned.

456
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:08,790
Well, since we went
on three-way dates yesterday,

457
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,792
odds are, we'll do
the same thing today, right?

458
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:11,752
Mm-hmm.

459
00:20:11,835 --> 00:20:13,879
And, well, you'll find out eventually,

460
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:17,007
but I wanted to tell you in advance
so it doesn't come as a surprise to you.

461
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:20,302
- You will be going on one of these dates.
- Oh, really? Why?

462
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:21,678
- Because I chose you.
- Oh, really?

463
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:23,972
Why is he telling her that now?

464
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:27,768
I had a general plan
for how this day would go,

465
00:20:27,851 --> 00:20:31,396
and I predicted that we'd be doing
three-way dates again,

466
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,564
but the men's version.

467
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:36,735
I started off with the assumption
that if three of us went on a date today,

468
00:20:36,818 --> 00:20:38,820
it would be awkward, no matter what.

469
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:42,241
So here's my plan. I'm going to use
the three-way date to have fun,

470
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:45,994
which is why I put cookies with characters
drawn on them in your mailbox.

471
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:47,162
Really?

472
00:20:47,246 --> 00:20:49,706
THIS MORNING

473
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,585
I bought some cookies at the Post Office

474
00:20:53,669 --> 00:20:56,004
and put them in Seo-yoon's mailbox.

475
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:58,090
You could say that was the kickoff.

476
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:02,636
I put them in there early in the morning
to kick things off.

477
00:21:04,388 --> 00:21:06,515
- Can you bring them with you?
- I should check… Oh, I'll go and…

478
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:08,350
Bring them with you
so we can snack on them,

479
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:10,060
and let's talk properly in the evening.

480
00:21:10,143 --> 00:21:11,687
- I think that might be--
- Yes, sounds good.

481
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:14,439
"Let's save the important topics
for later in the evening,

482
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:15,691
in a more comfortable setting."

483
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:19,945
I came up with that plan in the morning,
then talked to her separately.

484
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:21,655
Mm-hmm, understood.

485
00:21:21,738 --> 00:21:23,031
Then I'll see you later.

486
00:21:23,907 --> 00:21:25,450
Oh, sorry, it's my ring.

487
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:28,245
So the cookies is way of saying,

488
00:21:28,328 --> 00:21:31,456
"Even if we go on a three-way date,
you are my top pick."

489
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,208
Exactly. It's him telling her,

490
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:36,420
"Even if we're three, don't get flustered.
Let's just have fun."

491
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:39,631
But who was actually
the most flustered one there?

492
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:42,634
He was. That's what I don't get.

493
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:45,929
I'm going to the Post Office.

494
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:48,390
Oh, it's cold.

495
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,687
She'll be so surprised
when she opens it and sees all her gifts.

496
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,564
You're in for a surprise, Su-ji.

497
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:03,697
I wanted to grab
some writing paper just in case.

498
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:06,616
And since I was there, I took a look, and…

499
00:22:10,245 --> 00:22:11,455
Huh?

500
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:13,957
What's all that?

501
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:17,711
Who could it be?

502
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:23,383
There were two gifts and two letters.

503
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:26,970
I had thought I might
have received one gift,

504
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:29,431
but I never imagined I'd receive two.

505
00:22:30,057 --> 00:22:32,517
It made me stop short and go,

506
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:34,603
"Why are there two? What's going on?"

507
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:37,022
Who could it be?

508
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:40,901
Who could it be?

509
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:44,529
I wonder who it is?

510
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:51,787
I was so curious
that I opened one of them first,

511
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:56,875
and it was from one of the people
I had expected.

512
00:22:59,503 --> 00:23:00,879
It was from Jung-yun.

513
00:23:00,962 --> 00:23:02,756
I had mentioned I was needing hand cream.

514
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:03,673
JUNG-YUN

515
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:07,844
It said that he wanted to have
a one-on-one conversation with me.

516
00:23:07,928 --> 00:23:10,639
- He has pretty handwriting.
- He really applied himself.

517
00:23:10,722 --> 00:23:12,599
I already knew this to some extent,

518
00:23:12,682 --> 00:23:14,893
so I was like, "Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, I see."

519
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:16,061
Hmm…

520
00:23:17,437 --> 00:23:18,438
Hmm.

521
00:23:19,022 --> 00:23:20,982
She's going to be
really surprised by Jin-woo's.

522
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:22,859
Jin-woo's interest will be new to her.

523
00:23:22,943 --> 00:23:25,612
And then I opened the second letter, and…

524
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:28,115
What?

525
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:31,660
It was from someone
I didn't expect at all.

526
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:35,580
Now, she's going inside
to take a proper look.

527
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:38,458
Uh-huh, it's different
from just looking at it while walking.

528
00:23:46,216 --> 00:23:48,844
I opened the second letter
and it was from Jin-woo.

529
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:49,761
JIN-WOO

530
00:23:49,845 --> 00:23:53,932
In the lounge, I'd mentioned
losing a pair of gloves, and…

531
00:23:54,015 --> 00:23:55,934
Where did I put my gloves?

532
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:57,936
- You still haven't found them?
- No.

533
00:23:58,019 --> 00:24:00,730
I'm offering a reward to anyone
who can find my gloves.

534
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:03,775
I guess he heard me say that.

535
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:06,486
He had given me a letter
and a pair of gloves.

536
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,780
It's getting serious.

537
00:24:09,781 --> 00:24:11,199
It's driving me crazy.

538
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:14,953
When I read the letter,
I was absolutely shocked

539
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:19,040
because I really had no idea
that Jin-woo was interested in me.

540
00:24:19,833 --> 00:24:22,878
I was under the impression
he was interested in Jeong-eun.

541
00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:27,299
But since I knew Jeong-eun
was interested in Jin-woo…

542
00:24:27,382 --> 00:24:28,592
AFTER YESTERDAY'S DAY

543
00:24:28,675 --> 00:24:30,469
After today's conversation,

544
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:33,638
I feel like I have a better idea
of my rankings.

545
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:36,349
But it's not like Hyuk-joon's
fallen in the rankings,

546
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:38,059
but more like Jin-woo's risen again.

547
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:39,060
Mmm.

548
00:24:39,561 --> 00:24:41,521
I wasn't sure what to do.

549
00:24:41,605 --> 00:24:43,982
In the end, I felt even more confused.

550
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:46,193
- It's complicated.
- She's in an awkward spot.

551
00:24:46,276 --> 00:24:48,153
- A lot to deal with.
- What should I do?

552
00:24:49,654 --> 00:24:51,031
I can't let it show.

553
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:55,410
What should I say to Jeong-eun?

554
00:24:58,288 --> 00:24:59,498
Don't let it show.

555
00:25:00,373 --> 00:25:02,834
It's also not surprising
that Su-ji's shocked

556
00:25:02,918 --> 00:25:05,253
since Jin-woo didn't express himself
at all at Sparks House.

557
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:06,171
Right.

558
00:25:06,254 --> 00:25:08,006
It must be a real shock to her, seriously.

559
00:25:08,089 --> 00:25:10,425
It's like discovering the husband
in <i>Reply 1997.</i>

560
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:11,384
Right.

561
00:25:11,468 --> 00:25:13,470
We're trying to guess
who will be Su-ji's man.

562
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:15,680
So who do you think will be Su-ji's man?

563
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:19,059
It can't be. Please.

564
00:25:19,142 --> 00:25:20,519
Hurry up. Come check it out.

565
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:22,938
- I'll get up, just in case.
- No, I didn't get one.

566
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:24,189
- "Will be sold."
- "Will be sold."

567
00:25:24,272 --> 00:25:27,484
TODAY'S 5 MINUTE LIBRARY KEYS
WILL BE SOLD AT THE POST OFFICE

568
00:25:27,567 --> 00:25:30,111
It says it's only available
to the first two.

569
00:25:30,195 --> 00:25:32,489
- It's first come, first served.
- Run, run, run.

570
00:25:32,572 --> 00:25:35,033
- Jung-yun's also running.
- How do we buy them?

571
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:37,661
- But what do we buy them with?
- With what?

572
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:38,745
Hey!

573
00:25:39,829 --> 00:25:40,705
Whoa!

574
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:42,582
- Whoa!
- Be careful. Be careful.

575
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:44,709
Girl, wow.

576
00:25:44,793 --> 00:25:47,462
I'm sorry, but I really want this.

577
00:25:47,546 --> 00:25:48,588
No, but wait!

578
00:25:48,672 --> 00:25:50,006
No, but wait!

579
00:25:50,924 --> 00:25:54,094
What do we buy them with, though?
Where are they?

580
00:25:56,096 --> 00:25:58,223
- Oh, here it is.
- No, it's mine!

581
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:00,141
Two coupons?

582
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:02,060
So they have to use their own coupons?

583
00:26:02,143 --> 00:26:03,895
No, wait, they cost two coupons.

584
00:26:03,979 --> 00:26:06,856
I don't have my coupons on me!
Where are they?

585
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:10,068
Ugh! Oh, no, so this means
we have to run again!

586
00:26:10,735 --> 00:26:12,195
We have to run again.

587
00:26:13,363 --> 00:26:14,781
Are you kidding me?

588
00:26:16,032 --> 00:26:16,992
Seriously!

589
00:26:20,704 --> 00:26:23,248
When they said
it was first come, first served,

590
00:26:23,832 --> 00:26:25,584
I thought I had to run out and get it.

591
00:26:29,713 --> 00:26:30,922
Are you okay? You okay?

592
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:33,174
- Maybe we should pass on this?
- Uh-huh. What is it?

593
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:35,051
- Why?
- Two coupons is a lot.

594
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:38,305
I'm getting confused now.

595
00:26:38,388 --> 00:26:41,516
I thought I wanted to win that one,
but now I'm here…

596
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,852
- So hold on, two coupons?
- Seriously?

597
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:45,895
Uh, it's a bit overpriced.

598
00:26:45,979 --> 00:26:47,897
Do they expect us
to use two coupons on this?

599
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:50,066
Guys, why aren't you running?

600
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:51,484
We're not doing it.

601
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:54,070
I get it. Two coupons
is a pretty steep asking price.

602
00:26:54,154 --> 00:26:56,197
- We ran, but then…
- Two coupons, that's…

603
00:26:56,281 --> 00:26:58,033
- Way too much.
- It's expensive.

604
00:26:58,116 --> 00:27:00,035
I guess it's been settled.

605
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:01,828
They're so loud.

606
00:27:01,911 --> 00:27:03,872
We went all the way over,
then saw the cost.

607
00:27:03,955 --> 00:27:05,165
No way, no how.

608
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:06,374
What do you buy them with?

609
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,084
- Two coupons.
- Wow!

610
00:27:08,168 --> 00:27:10,629
That's too rich for my blood.
So we're still thinking it over.

611
00:27:10,712 --> 00:27:12,505
- A bit too expensive.
- Exactly.

612
00:27:12,589 --> 00:27:13,923
Two coupons is expensive.

613
00:27:14,007 --> 00:27:17,260
Uh, it's not like they're asking you
to pay real money.

614
00:27:17,344 --> 00:27:19,596
They get three coupons.
They get three each.

615
00:27:19,679 --> 00:27:22,223
But they have to use two
to use the 5 Minute Library.

616
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:23,516
Right, right.

617
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:26,978
But if they utilize it well, it becomes,
"I spent a whopping two coupons."

618
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:28,730
"That's how much I'm interested in you"?

619
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:30,607
You can use it as a flex
to flirt with someone.

620
00:27:30,690 --> 00:27:31,566
Show you care.

621
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,943
"I was willing to spend it
to find out how you feel."

622
00:27:34,027 --> 00:27:35,779
You see how this
could have been their play?

623
00:27:35,862 --> 00:27:38,823
But they're all going, "Yikes, I can't
afford this, it's too many coupons."

624
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:41,159
Has anyone bought it? I can't tell.

625
00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:43,161
Jung-yun hasn't returned,
so maybe he bought one?

626
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:52,170
I wanted to check out Su-ji's diary.

627
00:27:52,253 --> 00:27:53,922
TOP FIRST IMPRESSION PICK?
YOON JUNG-YUN

628
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:55,840
Oh, boy! Yes, he needed to see this.

629
00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:57,217
BEST ROTATION DATE?
JUNG-YUN

630
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:58,385
WHICH TWO TO GO
TO SPARKS HOUSE WITH?

631
00:27:58,468 --> 00:27:59,302
JUNG-YUN
SEUNG-HYUN

632
00:27:59,386 --> 00:28:00,220
- Good for him.
- Right.

633
00:28:01,554 --> 00:28:04,808
I was the first one
to arrive there with the coupons.

634
00:28:04,891 --> 00:28:07,352
I held the key
and thought it over for a while.

635
00:28:07,435 --> 00:28:08,812
So he hasn't seen it yet?

636
00:28:08,895 --> 00:28:09,938
Hurry up and buy it, Jung-yun.

637
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:11,773
- Buy it!
- You of all people should buy it!

638
00:28:13,316 --> 00:28:14,609
- Buy it!
- Whoa!

639
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:15,735
Yeah, yeah!

640
00:28:15,819 --> 00:28:16,820
I won't buy it.

641
00:28:17,654 --> 00:28:19,531
After thinking about it, I realized

642
00:28:19,614 --> 00:28:22,784
I don't have a burning desire to use
two whole coupons to read the diaries.

643
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:24,119
Don't leave yet.

644
00:28:24,202 --> 00:28:26,538
Hey, I'll send you the coupons!

645
00:28:26,621 --> 00:28:29,082
Oh, God, that crazy bastard!

646
00:28:29,165 --> 00:28:30,583
That didn't just happen.

647
00:28:30,667 --> 00:28:32,127
Where was that burning desire?

648
00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:33,712
Why didn't he have a burning desire?

649
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:36,005
What are you even saving them up for,
those coupons?

650
00:28:36,089 --> 00:28:37,424
Will they even be useful again?

651
00:28:37,507 --> 00:28:39,092
- Don't regret it later, buddy.
- Wow.

652
00:28:39,175 --> 00:28:41,136
- Don't regret it.
- I'm at a loss for words.

653
00:28:42,637 --> 00:28:44,806
- Again…
- I don't even know what to say.

654
00:28:44,889 --> 00:28:46,599
What should we do about Jung-yun, guys?

655
00:28:46,683 --> 00:28:48,435
- A loss for words.
- Man, this is…

656
00:28:48,518 --> 00:28:50,937
That line of, "I don't think
I had a burning desire," was just…

657
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:52,689
I mean, didn't he just have an awakening?

658
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:54,524
I know. He felt the need
to change and everything.

659
00:28:54,607 --> 00:28:55,817
He was gonna show more initiative.

660
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:59,487
Come on, if Jung-yun could see how
Su-ji answered "Jung-yun" every question,

661
00:28:59,571 --> 00:29:01,698
it would put his mind at ease
before the date,

662
00:29:01,781 --> 00:29:03,324
and he'd be a lot more assertive.

663
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:05,952
That's why it's so important
to make the right choices in life.

664
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:09,247
Life's about C, the choices
that come between B and D,

665
00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:10,582
birth and death.

666
00:29:11,624 --> 00:29:13,585
- Quote of the day by yours truly.
- You nailed it.

667
00:29:14,210 --> 00:29:17,046
Do you think they'll sell out? The keys?

668
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:19,549
- So no one bought one?
- That's right.

669
00:29:19,632 --> 00:29:20,800
No one bought one.

670
00:29:22,343 --> 00:29:24,220
- Should I?
- Two coupons is a lot.

671
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:26,723
I'll check it out.

672
00:29:26,806 --> 00:29:28,141
Really?

673
00:29:28,224 --> 00:29:30,518
Call it an impulse purchase.

674
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:32,312
Oh…

675
00:29:32,395 --> 00:29:34,981
What if you cough up two coupons
and the contents are disappointing?

676
00:29:35,064 --> 00:29:36,524
Uh, you have a point.

677
00:29:37,567 --> 00:29:41,237
In the beginning, I was hesitant
because it required two coupons,

678
00:29:41,321 --> 00:29:43,615
which was a bit more expensive
than I expected,

679
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:47,327
but I bought it because I decided
I had to enter the 5 Minute Library.

680
00:29:48,912 --> 00:29:50,121
Oh, you're buying one?

681
00:29:50,205 --> 00:29:51,581
You're buying one.

682
00:29:52,415 --> 00:29:55,752
Me? I'm thinking of reselling it.

683
00:29:55,835 --> 00:29:58,588
A MOMENT AGO

684
00:29:58,671 --> 00:30:00,548
Uh, while everyone was relaxing,

685
00:30:00,632 --> 00:30:03,593
thinking no one would buy the keys
as they were too expensive,

686
00:30:03,676 --> 00:30:07,222
I got motivated by a streak of defiance
to use the Library.

687
00:30:07,847 --> 00:30:10,016
Well, I came here to buy one.

688
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:11,643
Fine.

689
00:30:12,227 --> 00:30:14,229
They're sold. We took it off their hands.

690
00:30:14,312 --> 00:30:15,814
Wanna go first?

691
00:30:15,897 --> 00:30:17,732
- Oh? Is that okay?
- Uh-huh. Go ahead.

692
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:19,859
Ooh, okay, okay, okay.

693
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:26,199
Let's brag to the others.

694
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:29,577
What? Tae-hoon bought one?

695
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:31,329
- Who bought one?
- Did he open the door?

696
00:30:31,412 --> 00:30:33,373
- Hey, that's just, ah…
- No way!

697
00:30:33,456 --> 00:30:34,833
There goes our chance, then.

698
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:38,211
- I did not see that coming.
- I didn't see that coming.

699
00:30:38,294 --> 00:30:40,547
Tae-hoon must know exactly
what he's looking for.

700
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:42,465
- It's you.
- Yes, Soo-hyun.

701
00:30:42,549 --> 00:30:44,801
- That's you.
- And you don't even know it.

702
00:30:44,884 --> 00:30:47,512
- Who's he going to check? Soo-hyun?
- Ah, that's adorable.

703
00:30:51,224 --> 00:30:53,393
I checked Soo-hyun's diary.

704
00:30:54,102 --> 00:30:56,563
- Skim through all of it and memorize.
- Memorize.

705
00:30:57,146 --> 00:30:58,815
We had a chance to talk recently,

706
00:30:58,898 --> 00:31:01,985
so I was curious about her
and I checked her diary.

707
00:31:04,153 --> 00:31:05,154
What?

708
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:13,162
I checked out the new release.

709
00:31:13,246 --> 00:31:15,540
She wrote she had
the best conversation with me…

710
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:19,502
…which brought a smile to my face.

711
00:31:19,586 --> 00:31:21,129
Oh, during the Rotation Date?

712
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:25,258
The simple fact that she had
written down my name was exciting.

713
00:31:25,341 --> 00:31:28,261
On the third day, I finally
got to join the ranks as a participant

714
00:31:28,344 --> 00:31:30,722
instead of a bystander,
so that was exciting.

715
00:31:31,222 --> 00:31:33,766
Those coupons were definitely
worth it for him, wouldn't you agree?

716
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:35,268
- Totally.
- Never doubted it.

717
00:31:37,353 --> 00:31:39,814
- Oh, he looks totally stoked.
- I know, right?

718
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:42,025
- It was really, really worth it.
- Oh, really?

719
00:31:42,108 --> 00:31:43,610
I guess they added some new information.

720
00:31:43,693 --> 00:31:45,570
- Did they add to it?
- Uh-huh, I think so.

721
00:31:45,653 --> 00:31:46,946
I got to check both of them.

722
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:49,198
Wait, you read the new release
and the old one?

723
00:31:49,282 --> 00:31:50,283
Of course.

724
00:31:50,366 --> 00:31:52,410
- Of course.
- You can check both.

725
00:31:52,493 --> 00:31:53,328
Right, ah.

726
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:55,914
If he tells Soo-hyun later…

727
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:57,790
- "Actually, it's you"?
- "Actually, it's you."

728
00:31:57,874 --> 00:32:00,043
- I'd… I'd be so moved.
- Same, same.

729
00:32:00,126 --> 00:32:02,295
And everyone else
was so reluctant to use them.

730
00:32:02,378 --> 00:32:04,839
- Despite that general consensus…
- Right, right.

731
00:32:04,923 --> 00:32:06,883
And if someone
who's just been messing around

732
00:32:06,966 --> 00:32:08,343
suddenly makes their move on you…

733
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:09,636
Uh-huh.

734
00:32:09,719 --> 00:32:12,388
That's totally like in <i>Reply 1997,</i>
I'm serious.

735
00:32:13,389 --> 00:32:14,599
- He's happy.
- Wow.

736
00:32:14,682 --> 00:32:16,351
You seem so happy right now.

737
00:32:16,935 --> 00:32:18,436
Please, keep rolling the footage.

738
00:32:18,519 --> 00:32:20,688
He's in a rush now.

739
00:32:22,649 --> 00:32:23,733
Here we go.

740
00:32:30,239 --> 00:32:32,492
I chose to read Jin-woo's diary.

741
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:38,748
I wanted to know his thoughts
on an ideal partner, so I opened it.

742
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:41,542
She's reading the contents
of the new release.

743
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:46,339
WHO WAS YOUR TOP FIRST
IMPRESSION PICK? HAN SU-JI

744
00:32:46,422 --> 00:32:48,299
- Ahh…
- Hmm, Su-ji.

745
00:32:54,097 --> 00:32:57,433
WHO DID YOU HAVE THE BEST
ROTATION DATE WITH? HAN SU-JI

746
00:33:01,562 --> 00:33:03,189
WHICH TWO TO GO
TO SPARKS HOUSE WITH?

747
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:04,107
SU-JI, JEONG-EUN

748
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:05,900
- She's nowhere.
- She's not even in his top two.

749
00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:20,581
Unfortunately, I didn't
see my name anywhere in his new release.

750
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:25,712
I thought we had
some good conversations together.

751
00:33:27,422 --> 00:33:29,424
The only thing he said about me

752
00:33:29,507 --> 00:33:32,552
was that he had a decent
first impression of me.

753
00:33:33,219 --> 00:33:35,722
Actually, when I first got here,
I was asked,

754
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:38,683
who left the biggest impression on me,
and I also said it was you.

755
00:33:38,766 --> 00:33:39,976
Mmm, mmm.

756
00:33:41,978 --> 00:33:45,398
But I think I misinterpreted that to mean
that I was his top first impression pick.

757
00:33:45,481 --> 00:33:47,275
WHO WAS YOUR NUMBER ONE
FIRST IMPRESSION? SU-JI

758
00:33:47,942 --> 00:33:51,404
I came to think, "Ah, I guess
I didn't have a place in his heart

759
00:33:51,487 --> 00:33:52,613
to begin with."

760
00:33:53,322 --> 00:33:56,367
I didn't feel great about it
and I couldn't hide my feelings.

761
00:33:56,451 --> 00:33:58,202
I'd spent so much for this.

762
00:33:58,286 --> 00:33:59,746
I left shocked and upset.

763
00:34:02,707 --> 00:34:04,542
Oh, no, Han-ju.

764
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:08,254
TAE-HOON'S - JUNG-YUN'S
JIN-WOO'S - HYUK-JUN'S

765
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:09,797
Ah…

766
00:34:10,465 --> 00:34:13,134
- It'll be hard to hide her feelings.
- "Did I kind of misunderstand?"

767
00:34:13,926 --> 00:34:15,428
Han-ju must be so upset.

768
00:34:15,511 --> 00:34:19,140
They were really vibing
during that conversation in the car.

769
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:21,893
Her feelings for him
must have grown a lot.

770
00:34:21,976 --> 00:34:23,978
Ah, but I can't help but worry.

771
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:27,815
What if Han-ju ends up
staying at the dorm all on her own?

772
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:29,275
Then I guess day-drinking.

773
00:34:29,358 --> 00:34:32,403
Oh, God, no. Ah!

774
00:34:32,487 --> 00:34:34,489
TODAY, THE MALE SINGLES
WILL BE GOING ON THREE-WAY DATES

775
00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:35,656
Oh, they're doing this.

776
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:37,658
The opposite of what we did yesterday.

777
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:40,036
I got to pick my top and second picks.

778
00:34:40,119 --> 00:34:43,331
So I thought, "Ah, I'm finally
getting a chance to talk."

779
00:34:43,414 --> 00:34:46,334
When else would I get to go on a date
with two people like that?

780
00:34:46,417 --> 00:34:48,920
The three-way date format
gives you a lot of things

781
00:34:49,003 --> 00:34:51,464
to be mindful of and can be a headache,

782
00:34:51,547 --> 00:34:53,925
but I plan to make it funny and enjoyable.

783
00:34:54,008 --> 00:34:57,512
I have my hands full
just trying to figure out my own feelings,

784
00:34:57,595 --> 00:35:00,890
so I think I need to get a handle
on my own feelings first.

785
00:35:00,973 --> 00:35:03,392
I was hoping that the people I picked

786
00:35:03,476 --> 00:35:06,479
as my top and second picks
would pick me too,

787
00:35:06,562 --> 00:35:09,148
but at the same time,
I thought it was possible

788
00:35:09,232 --> 00:35:10,817
I wouldn't get picked at all,

789
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:13,361
and if I'm left alone,
that would really get to me.

790
00:35:13,444 --> 00:35:14,862
I felt pretty uneasy.

791
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:16,447
For the female singles,

792
00:35:16,531 --> 00:35:18,950
it's a chance to see if the person
they picked yesterday

793
00:35:19,033 --> 00:35:20,827
returned the favor
and picked them as well.

794
00:35:20,910 --> 00:35:21,744
You're right.

795
00:35:21,828 --> 00:35:23,871
It's Jung-yun's three-way date.

796
00:35:25,414 --> 00:35:28,668
I know who Jung-yun's top pick is,
but who would be his second pick?

797
00:35:30,753 --> 00:35:33,172
I wrote down
and submitted Su-ji as my top pick.

798
00:35:34,549 --> 00:35:35,758
YESTERDAY'S THREE-WAY DATE

799
00:35:35,842 --> 00:35:38,344
When I'm alone, I kind of have
this weird desire to be funny, so--

800
00:35:38,427 --> 00:35:41,264
Man, I really dressed up
to look fresh and lively.

801
00:35:41,347 --> 00:35:43,599
Right. He barely
got to talk to her that day.

802
00:35:43,683 --> 00:35:46,060
After getting back
from the three-way date,

803
00:35:46,144 --> 00:35:48,354
I was really conflicted.

804
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:53,317
And because I found out
that Jin-woo was the one

805
00:35:53,401 --> 00:35:55,945
who had put the letter in her mailbox,

806
00:35:56,028 --> 00:35:57,363
I was kind of on edge.

807
00:35:58,948 --> 00:36:03,119
I thought to myself, "I should muster up
the courage to tell her today."

808
00:36:03,202 --> 00:36:05,121
Wow, and he's looking great today.

809
00:36:10,626 --> 00:36:12,170
- Hello.
- Hello.

810
00:36:12,253 --> 00:36:14,046
Hello. Have you been waiting long?

811
00:36:14,130 --> 00:36:15,673
- Oh, not at all. I just got here.
- Ah.

812
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:17,550
SU-JI
JUNG-YUN'S TOP PICK

813
00:36:17,633 --> 00:36:18,551
- Hello.
- Hello.

814
00:36:18,634 --> 00:36:19,802
- Aren't you cold?
- Huh?

815
00:36:19,886 --> 00:36:22,305
- Are you okay? Aren't you cold?
- I'm okay. How about you? You okay?

816
00:36:22,388 --> 00:36:23,598
I'm okay.

817
00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:29,729
So, I went to the Post Office
this morning…

818
00:36:29,812 --> 00:36:30,938
Okay.

819
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:32,523
- I saw the gift.
- You saw it?

820
00:36:32,607 --> 00:36:35,193
So I brought the hand cream.
Do you want to see it?

821
00:36:35,276 --> 00:36:37,403
- She's bringing it up right away.
- Hand cream.

822
00:36:37,945 --> 00:36:39,780
Things are looking good so far.

823
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:42,033
- It smells really nice.
- Oh, good.

824
00:36:42,116 --> 00:36:43,576
I think you picked well. Good choice.

825
00:36:43,659 --> 00:36:45,203
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

826
00:36:45,286 --> 00:36:47,246
- I also read your letter.
- Yeah.

827
00:36:47,330 --> 00:36:51,083
Do you often have the opportunity
to write letters to people?

828
00:36:51,584 --> 00:36:55,004
Hmm, I'd say not really.

829
00:36:55,087 --> 00:36:57,131
- You don't? Mmm…
- No, I don't.

830
00:36:57,632 --> 00:36:59,717
You know, with the written word,

831
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:02,011
there's a certain sincerity
you can convey.

832
00:37:02,094 --> 00:37:03,512
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

833
00:37:03,596 --> 00:37:07,475
I think I only write letters
when I want to achieve that.

834
00:37:08,142 --> 00:37:09,227
I see.

835
00:37:10,186 --> 00:37:14,357
So in that letter, I wrote at the end,
"I'll be waiting for your reply."

836
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:18,152
Were you planning
on writing back, by any chance?

837
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:20,821
Oh, my God, he's doing it again. Ugh!

838
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:22,782
Why does he keep doing that?

839
00:37:22,865 --> 00:37:24,575
Why do you keep quizzing her so much?

840
00:37:24,659 --> 00:37:26,619
And what's with all this,
"I did this for you once,

841
00:37:26,702 --> 00:37:28,579
so you should also
do it for me once," crap?

842
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:30,831
- Why do you keep quizzing her?
- I don't know anymore.

843
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:32,917
- I mean…
- Jung-yun…

844
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,710
- Jung-yun's a bit…
- You're his cupid.

845
00:37:34,794 --> 00:37:37,922
He's the type of guy who would
ask his bride at his own wedding:

846
00:37:38,005 --> 00:37:42,009
"Were you not going to read your vows
if I hadn't read my vows first?"

847
00:37:43,052 --> 00:37:46,097
"Can you read yours first?
Can you put the ring on me first?"

848
00:37:46,180 --> 00:37:47,473
"Can you walk out first?"

849
00:37:47,556 --> 00:37:49,016
He keeps quizzing her!

850
00:37:49,100 --> 00:37:51,519
He gives off the vibe of someone
who expects the other person

851
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:53,020
to keep doing something for him.

852
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:56,440
I wrote at the end,
"I'll be waiting for your reply."

853
00:37:56,524 --> 00:37:58,234
Were you planning on writing back?

854
00:37:58,317 --> 00:38:00,695
Writing back? I was just going
to reply to you in person.

855
00:38:00,778 --> 00:38:03,322
- Oh, okay.
- That's the kind of reaction you'll get.

856
00:38:03,406 --> 00:38:05,199
"When should we do it again?"

857
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:07,285
I meant, if you ended up
finding out about it late.

858
00:38:07,368 --> 00:38:08,995
- Ah…
- Yeah.

859
00:38:14,208 --> 00:38:15,251
I, uh…

860
00:38:16,711 --> 00:38:18,462
You see, all this time,

861
00:38:19,171 --> 00:38:23,509
I used to think I could only
fall for the people I was attracted to.

862
00:38:24,218 --> 00:38:28,764
But you, um, have been expressing
your feelings for me.

863
00:38:28,848 --> 00:38:30,308
Whether it was your first impression…

864
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:32,351
Mmm, right. Since I was interested in you.

865
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:34,312
When you expressed your interest in me,

866
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:37,273
that was actually…
that had never happened to me.

867
00:38:37,356 --> 00:38:38,983
- Really. Seriously.
- Oh, really? Uh-huh.

868
00:38:39,066 --> 00:38:41,068
That's it. Open up to her.
Tell her how you're feeling.

869
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:42,236
That's it. Take your time.

870
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:44,155
Uh-huh, and that's why…

871
00:38:45,364 --> 00:38:49,076
I couldn't stop thinking about the way
you expressed your feelings for me.

872
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:52,288
- You couldn't stop? Oh.
- No, I couldn't stop thinking about it.

873
00:38:52,371 --> 00:38:56,167
So, I already told you
that I wanted to talk more with you,

874
00:38:56,250 --> 00:38:58,794
but the three-way date kinda placed
too many obstacles in our way.

875
00:38:58,878 --> 00:39:00,421
Because it's limiting? Uh-huh.

876
00:39:01,088 --> 00:39:04,717
I don't think I got to talk to you
properly on that date.

877
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:05,885
Mmm…

878
00:39:05,968 --> 00:39:08,220
Of course, this is also about to turn
into a three-way date.

879
00:39:08,304 --> 00:39:09,930
Right, since another person is coming.

880
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:11,140
But…

881
00:39:11,223 --> 00:39:13,893
So if you're okay with it, later,

882
00:39:13,976 --> 00:39:16,771
even if it's not within the context
of a three-way date…

883
00:39:16,854 --> 00:39:18,147
In the evening when we get back?

884
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,440
Yeah, uh-huh, in the evening.

885
00:39:19,523 --> 00:39:21,275
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, okay.

886
00:39:21,359 --> 00:39:22,401
- Okay?
- Okay.

887
00:39:22,485 --> 00:39:23,527
Nice.

888
00:39:26,238 --> 00:39:29,075
Have you ever given any serious thought
about your type?

889
00:39:29,158 --> 00:39:30,534
Like, your ideal woman?

890
00:39:32,328 --> 00:39:34,163
I want her to be a strong person.

891
00:39:35,164 --> 00:39:37,541
- Mm-hmm.
- Yes, I want her to be a strong person.

892
00:39:37,625 --> 00:39:40,669
Someone with a clearly
defined set of values, yeah.

893
00:39:40,753 --> 00:39:42,713
What I mean by that is someone

894
00:39:42,797 --> 00:39:45,716
who has a clear idea
of their likes and dislikes.

895
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,134
That's why…

896
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:48,636
Oh, who could this be?

897
00:39:49,595 --> 00:39:50,971
She's his second pick?

898
00:39:51,055 --> 00:39:52,681
Oh, so Jeong-eun was his second pick?

899
00:39:52,765 --> 00:39:54,183
Jeong-eun's coming.

900
00:39:55,184 --> 00:39:58,270
- Jeong-eun. Do you want to sit here?
- Oh, all right.

901
00:39:58,354 --> 00:40:01,774
JEONG-EUN
JUNG-YUN'S SECOND PICK

902
00:40:03,401 --> 00:40:05,194
- Hello.
- Hello.

903
00:40:05,277 --> 00:40:06,821
- Hello.
- Hello.

904
00:40:12,535 --> 00:40:13,953
I was really surprised.

905
00:40:14,036 --> 00:40:17,623
It hadn't crossed my mind
that Jung-yun was interested in me at all.

906
00:40:17,706 --> 00:40:21,335
I was surprised because
I hadn't anticipated this situation.

907
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:23,963
THE WOMEN DON'T KNOW
WHICH ONE OF THEM

908
00:40:24,046 --> 00:40:25,005
IS THE TOP OR SECOND PICK

909
00:40:25,881 --> 00:40:28,175
Oh, well, let me just finish
what I was saying.

910
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:29,260
Huh?

911
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:35,015
Let me just answer her and wrap this up.

912
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:37,268
Huh? I don't think
continuing that conversation

913
00:40:37,351 --> 00:40:38,561
would be appropriate right now.

914
00:40:38,644 --> 00:40:40,980
This definitely isn't a date
you can handle.

915
00:40:41,605 --> 00:40:42,648
The reason is…

916
00:40:42,731 --> 00:40:44,191
Huh? You're doing that right now?

917
00:40:44,275 --> 00:40:47,319
- You definitely can't handle this date.
- Jung-yun…

918
00:40:47,403 --> 00:40:52,616
Hmm, I don't think I'd feel
very attracted to someone

919
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:56,537
who gets swayed too easily by others.

920
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:58,122
Is that so? Hmm.

921
00:40:59,331 --> 00:41:01,208
- We were talking about our ideal partners.
- Ah.

922
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:04,128
And he said he likes someone who's strong
and doesn't get swayed easily,

923
00:41:04,211 --> 00:41:06,005
so I asked him why.

924
00:41:14,346 --> 00:41:17,224
Wow. That guy's something else, right?

925
00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:19,518
Wow, I did not think
he would finish saying that.

926
00:41:19,602 --> 00:41:21,562
- They're like racehorses.
- They really are.

927
00:41:21,645 --> 00:41:23,314
Our eternal singles are like racehorses.

928
00:41:23,397 --> 00:41:25,191
Jung-yun is interested in Su-ji right now,

929
00:41:25,274 --> 00:41:27,818
so he wants to tell her about
his ideal woman as soon as possible.

930
00:41:27,902 --> 00:41:30,112
- Right, that's why he's such in a rush.
- Right.

931
00:41:31,906 --> 00:41:34,116
I'm actually pretty curious about this.

932
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:36,702
Would you mind if I also
asked you the reason why?

933
00:41:36,785 --> 00:41:39,079
You guys were just my top
and second picks.

934
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:41,582
- Do not reveal their rankings.
- Give it to them straight.

935
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:42,750
- Can I be honest?
- Don't do it!

936
00:41:42,833 --> 00:41:44,251
- Of course.
- Uh-huh, uh-huh.

937
00:41:44,335 --> 00:41:45,628
Wow, I'm nervous.

938
00:41:46,212 --> 00:41:47,671
Look how nervous Su-ji is.

939
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:50,424
To be honest, there's a bit of a gap
between you two.

940
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:52,176
- Oh.
- Yeah, just a bit.

941
00:41:52,259 --> 00:41:54,470
- Well, I'm not surprised at all.
- Oh, you're not?

942
00:41:54,553 --> 00:41:57,181
For me, the real shock lies in the fact
that I'm actually here.

943
00:41:57,264 --> 00:41:59,433
Oh, that's the real shocker?
'Cause the thing is,

944
00:42:00,017 --> 00:42:01,435
I don't really have a second pick.

945
00:42:01,519 --> 00:42:02,478
Mm-hmm.

946
00:42:02,561 --> 00:42:06,440
So I just picked someone
I wanted to talk more with, I guess.

947
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:08,943
- Someone I barely got to talk to yet.
- That's who you picked. Mm-hmm.

948
00:42:09,026 --> 00:42:10,778
That's who I picked. That's right.

949
00:42:10,861 --> 00:42:12,196
- No, no, I don't mind.
- That's why.

950
00:42:12,279 --> 00:42:14,865
I actually prefer it
when people give it to me straight.

951
00:42:16,492 --> 00:42:21,497
So yesterday was a turning point for me,
where I started to think deeply about--

952
00:42:21,580 --> 00:42:23,541
Oh, yes, I heard how you kept
playing the piano.

953
00:42:24,625 --> 00:42:26,752
- Sorry. I told her.
- I heard you were the piano man yesterday.

954
00:42:26,835 --> 00:42:29,838
Oh, really? To be honest,
I wanted to play it for you.

955
00:42:29,922 --> 00:42:33,509
- Oh, really?
- Mm-hmm. But you were not around.

956
00:42:33,592 --> 00:42:36,053
- Oh, my, this… this is a first for me.
- Really?

957
00:42:36,136 --> 00:42:39,265
- I'm actually feeling a little flustered.
- Are you uncomfortable?

958
00:42:39,348 --> 00:42:42,476
Oh, no, no, I didn't mean that
in a bad way, not at all.

959
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:45,771
Do you have a preference?
Which cake would you like to try?

960
00:42:45,854 --> 00:42:49,567
They both look pretty similar,
but I want the red one.

961
00:42:49,650 --> 00:42:51,110
The red one?

962
00:42:51,193 --> 00:42:54,196
- First the ketchup, and now the cake?
- Oh, where is this going?

963
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,282
- You seem to really click with red.
- Red.

964
00:42:56,365 --> 00:42:58,492
Oh, no, she looks a little uncomfortable.

965
00:42:58,576 --> 00:43:01,328
He should still take care
of Jeong-eun too.

966
00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:02,830
I was really flustered.

967
00:43:02,913 --> 00:43:05,833
It was like being in the live audience
of a TV show.

968
00:43:05,916 --> 00:43:10,337
It kinda felt like if I was hosting
a talk show, if you will.

969
00:43:10,421 --> 00:43:12,464
The seating arrangement in itself

970
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:14,717
made me feel like
I was hosting their date,

971
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:17,886
so that thought
did actually cross my mind.

972
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:20,097
That's true.

973
00:43:20,180 --> 00:43:22,683
- Also like a referee of a battle of idols.
- Right.

974
00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:26,103
- Just pretend I'm not here.
- Oh, no, we should all talk together.

975
00:43:26,186 --> 00:43:27,980
Oh, no, we're not doing that.
That's not right.

976
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:29,982
I think you'd have more fun
if you guys did that.

977
00:43:30,816 --> 00:43:34,361
I was ultimately very satisfied
with the outcome of this date

978
00:43:34,445 --> 00:43:37,948
because, even though I knew in advance
that this would be a three-way date,

979
00:43:38,032 --> 00:43:43,162
the first one there was Su-ji,
and then Jeong-eun arrived later.

980
00:43:43,245 --> 00:43:45,080
So before she got there,

981
00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:48,667
I told Su-Ji everything I wanted her
to know about my feelings.

982
00:43:49,543 --> 00:43:52,713
Finally, he confessed his love
even before Jeong-eun arrived.

983
00:43:52,796 --> 00:43:54,757
He might've changed too much now.

984
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:57,926
Well, it's a classic eternal single move.
Do what you want and go.

985
00:43:58,010 --> 00:43:59,386
Yeah, I think it went well.

986
00:44:00,220 --> 00:44:01,639
I want to know how Su-ji feels.

987
00:44:01,722 --> 00:44:04,016
Uh, what surprised me was that

988
00:44:04,099 --> 00:44:07,645
Jung-yun is even more my type
than I initially thought.

989
00:44:08,270 --> 00:44:10,189
He's very calm,

990
00:44:10,272 --> 00:44:14,276
he speaks really slowly,
and he's also very thoughtful.

991
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:17,613
Honestly, I don't exactly know
how he feels about me right now,

992
00:44:17,696 --> 00:44:21,241
but overall,
well, I came to the conclusion

993
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:24,286
that I should have a long
one-on-one conversation with him.

994
00:44:24,370 --> 00:44:25,496
- Ooh!
- Oh, wow.

995
00:44:25,579 --> 00:44:27,748
- That's a relief.
- At last it had a positive effect.

996
00:44:27,831 --> 00:44:29,375
- This is great.
- Thank goodness.

997
00:44:29,458 --> 00:44:32,252
The guys around him
wouldn't stop pining over Su-ji, right?

998
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:34,880
So the urgency made him tell her,
even with Jeong-eun there,

999
00:44:34,963 --> 00:44:36,882
"I love you, I like you."

1000
00:44:36,965 --> 00:44:40,010
- And that's good, fantastically good.
- Things worked out really well.

1001
00:44:40,094 --> 00:44:43,847
Fortunately, it had a somewhat
positive effect.

1002
00:44:43,931 --> 00:44:46,892
I think it's that Su-ji just likes
Jung-yun much more than we thought.

1003
00:44:46,975 --> 00:44:48,894
- I'm so glad.
- Gosh, I'm so nervous.

1004
00:44:48,977 --> 00:44:50,854
I'm so nervous, I could die.

1005
00:44:50,938 --> 00:44:52,147
Yes, thank you.

1006
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:53,232
TAE-HOON'S THREE-WAY DATE

1007
00:44:53,315 --> 00:44:55,484
- Oh, Kim Tae-hoon, let's go.
- Ooh.

1008
00:44:55,567 --> 00:44:57,194
Our character from <i>Reply.</i>

1009
00:44:57,277 --> 00:44:59,196
I joined the program a little late,

1010
00:44:59,279 --> 00:45:01,532
so today's three-way date
was an opportunity for me.

1011
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,294
Oh.

1012
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:15,921
- You're here.
- Howdy.

1013
00:45:16,004 --> 00:45:17,506
- Hello.
- Hello.

1014
00:45:17,589 --> 00:45:19,133
Oh, he's loving this.

1015
00:45:20,217 --> 00:45:22,010
Ooh.

1016
00:45:22,761 --> 00:45:24,221
- Nice to see you.
- Nice to see you.

1017
00:45:24,304 --> 00:45:25,514
Really nice to see you.

1018
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:29,435
To be honest, I felt good.

1019
00:45:29,518 --> 00:45:33,939
I was very grateful and excited
because he had chosen me.

1020
00:45:35,733 --> 00:45:37,401
Oh, I haven't had it yet.

1021
00:45:37,484 --> 00:45:38,944
- What?
- The blueberry smoothie.

1022
00:45:39,027 --> 00:45:41,822
- Maybe later then.
- I know. Man, I'm looking forward to it.

1023
00:45:41,905 --> 00:45:46,410
Seriously, though, I was really grateful
because I didn't feel like eating at all.

1024
00:45:47,661 --> 00:45:51,206
I kept thinking, "I should eat something,
but I have no appetite,"

1025
00:45:51,290 --> 00:45:53,333
but the smoothie brought back my appetite.

1026
00:45:54,668 --> 00:45:56,587
I'm glad you got to have it.

1027
00:45:57,171 --> 00:45:59,882
Yay, and again today.
It's going to be delicious.

1028
00:45:59,965 --> 00:46:01,467
- I saved it for you, didn't I?
- I know.

1029
00:46:01,550 --> 00:46:03,093
He's mistiming
every attempt at eye contact.

1030
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:04,678
Our Tae-hoon from <i>Reply.</i>

1031
00:46:04,762 --> 00:46:06,346
Yay, I get to have it when I get back.

1032
00:46:06,889 --> 00:46:10,851
I was happy that Soo-hyun noticed
that I was looking out for her.

1033
00:46:10,934 --> 00:46:13,103
He'll need to see
the return value, you see.

1034
00:46:13,771 --> 00:46:16,356
Were you expecting this? Not at all?

1035
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:19,568
I couldn't guess who it would be
because I…

1036
00:46:19,651 --> 00:46:21,779
I thought I wouldn't get to go
on a date at all.

1037
00:46:21,862 --> 00:46:25,699
I picked you because I enjoyed
our conversations.

1038
00:46:25,783 --> 00:46:26,992
Oh, oh.

1039
00:46:27,075 --> 00:46:28,076
- They're good.
- Thank you.

1040
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:31,079
- Hey, the coupons, tell her…
- Tell her about the coupons.

1041
00:46:31,163 --> 00:46:32,915
I did have so much fun
talking to you yesterday.

1042
00:46:32,998 --> 00:46:34,541
Mm-hmm, I also had fun.

1043
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:39,505
That's why I said yesterday
that you were one of my top, top picks.

1044
00:46:39,588 --> 00:46:40,589
Oh. Ah.

1045
00:46:41,340 --> 00:46:43,801
You were one of the people I'd been
wanting to have a conversation with.

1046
00:46:43,884 --> 00:46:44,718
Oh, really?

1047
00:46:44,802 --> 00:46:48,180
I wanted to have another
proper conversation with you.

1048
00:46:48,263 --> 00:46:49,723
Conversation? Mmm.

1049
00:46:49,807 --> 00:46:52,017
Yes. That's why he even
checked out your diary. Tell her.

1050
00:46:52,100 --> 00:46:54,019
Ugh, just hurry up and tell her!

1051
00:46:54,102 --> 00:46:56,230
Hurry, hurry and tell her! Hurry, hurry!

1052
00:46:57,898 --> 00:46:59,441
Have you been to the Post Office?

1053
00:46:59,525 --> 00:47:02,152
Not yet. Oh, at around 7:00
in the morning.

1054
00:47:02,778 --> 00:47:05,197
- You went there?
- Mm-hmm. Uh, I went to take a look.

1055
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:07,741
- He's doing it.
- Uh-huh, that's it.

1056
00:47:07,825 --> 00:47:10,619
Ugh, just hurry up
and tell her already. Come on!

1057
00:47:10,702 --> 00:47:12,496
- I didn't look inside, though.
- Oh, I know.

1058
00:47:12,579 --> 00:47:15,749
I mean, it wasn't worth
the two coupon investment.

1059
00:47:15,833 --> 00:47:17,709
- I don't think it was a bad investment.
- Oh.

1060
00:47:17,793 --> 00:47:19,461
Then you must have read someone's diary.

1061
00:47:19,545 --> 00:47:21,505
- Right.
- Were you satisfied with what you read?

1062
00:47:21,588 --> 00:47:23,006
- Whoa!
- Han-na!

1063
00:47:23,090 --> 00:47:24,091
We're almost there!

1064
00:47:25,008 --> 00:47:27,594
- I was satisfied.
- Do it, do it, tell her who it was.

1065
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:29,513
I don't think Soo-hyun
has noticed it at all.

1066
00:47:29,596 --> 00:47:31,723
He's just saying
they can communicate well together.

1067
00:47:31,807 --> 00:47:34,101
- Hey, it's you, you noodlehead!
- Hey, let's listen, quiet!

1068
00:47:34,184 --> 00:47:35,644
- It's you, Soo-hyun!
- Han-na, quiet down!

1069
00:47:35,727 --> 00:47:37,354
- It's you!
- We're there!

1070
00:47:37,437 --> 00:47:39,064
- Really? The new release?
- Mm-hmm.

1071
00:47:39,147 --> 00:47:40,566
Mm-hmm. Oh, I read it all.

1072
00:47:40,649 --> 00:47:41,733
- Both of them?
- Mm-hmm.

1073
00:47:41,817 --> 00:47:43,902
The new releases
don't have a lot of content.

1074
00:47:43,986 --> 00:47:45,404
Whose could you have read?

1075
00:47:46,655 --> 00:47:47,865
Will you tell me?

1076
00:47:48,490 --> 00:47:49,324
We'll see.

1077
00:47:49,408 --> 00:47:50,784
- Oh, gosh.
- Do it!

1078
00:47:50,868 --> 00:47:53,203
It's you! It's you.

1079
00:47:53,287 --> 00:47:55,914
You know, everyone
has a different look on their face

1080
00:47:55,998 --> 00:47:59,293
when they come out of there,
but you… you definitely seemed happy.

1081
00:47:59,376 --> 00:48:00,252
Mmm.

1082
00:48:00,919 --> 00:48:03,255
I did not want to talk
about my feelings for now.

1083
00:48:04,923 --> 00:48:09,511
I was worried that I might open up
my heart too early to be disappointed,

1084
00:48:09,595 --> 00:48:13,015
so, uh, I plan
to open up my heart cautiously.

1085
00:48:13,098 --> 00:48:15,225
No, there aren't that many days left.

1086
00:48:15,309 --> 00:48:17,603
- You have to hurry up and do it.
- If not, why use two coupons?

1087
00:48:17,686 --> 00:48:20,272
I think the smoothie yesterday
did bring us a lot closer, though.

1088
00:48:20,355 --> 00:48:22,190
Before that, there was also
the ten-minute date.

1089
00:48:22,274 --> 00:48:24,943
The ten-minute date was good,
but the smoothie really made us.

1090
00:48:26,236 --> 00:48:27,529
Who will enter next?

1091
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:31,825
What's going on here?

1092
00:48:31,909 --> 00:48:33,744
- Oh, hello. Hello.
- Hello.

1093
00:48:33,827 --> 00:48:36,580
But didn't Tae-hoon say
he was getting off the Su-ji Love Express?

1094
00:48:36,663 --> 00:48:38,123
Come to think of it, you're right.

1095
00:48:38,206 --> 00:48:40,083
That Tae-hoon's really something else.

1096
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:41,919
- You were getting off!
- "Su-ji Love Express."

1097
00:48:42,628 --> 00:48:44,421
- Hello.
- Nice to see you.

1098
00:48:44,504 --> 00:48:46,548
It's been forever
since we greeted each other.

1099
00:48:46,632 --> 00:48:48,133
Why do you keep avoiding me?

1100
00:48:48,216 --> 00:48:51,678
I didn't avoid you. I didn't avoid anyone.

1101
00:48:51,762 --> 00:48:53,764
- She doesn't look happy.
- No, she doesn't.

1102
00:48:53,847 --> 00:48:56,183
- Look at her.
- This one's good.

1103
00:48:56,266 --> 00:48:58,185
Wait, you thought I was avoiding you?

1104
00:48:58,268 --> 00:49:00,562
Well, ever since we got back that day.

1105
00:49:00,646 --> 00:49:04,066
Hey, I didn't avoid anyone.
What are you saying?

1106
00:49:04,149 --> 00:49:06,735
I mean, you just kept
looking straight ahead, and…

1107
00:49:06,818 --> 00:49:08,153
I've got front-row seats.

1108
00:49:08,236 --> 00:49:10,822
I see. I'm sorry.
But I promise I wasn't avoiding you.

1109
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:13,909
No, I mean, uh, there was, like,
an empty seat near me,

1110
00:49:13,992 --> 00:49:15,327
but you sat two seats away…

1111
00:49:15,410 --> 00:49:17,746
Oh, really? I didn't even know
I was doing that.

1112
00:49:17,829 --> 00:49:20,791
- So it's been bothering you, huh? Sorry.
- Yeah, well, so…

1113
00:49:20,874 --> 00:49:23,085
I'll just sit next to you from now on.

1114
00:49:23,168 --> 00:49:25,587
When there's an empty seat,
I'll just sit next to Tae-hoon.

1115
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:27,464
- "That's my seat. Move!"
- "Everyone, move aside."

1116
00:49:27,547 --> 00:49:30,384
Ah, I feel terrible about this. Seriously,
it's such an unfortunate situation.

1117
00:49:30,467 --> 00:49:33,053
He should have mentioned the Library
before she arrived.

1118
00:49:33,136 --> 00:49:34,972
Right now, what Soo-hyun's hearing

1119
00:49:35,055 --> 00:49:37,975
is that Tae-hoon's been
very interested in Su-ji all along.

1120
00:49:38,058 --> 00:49:40,644
- Uh-huh.
- I know. A total waste of time, this is.

1121
00:49:40,727 --> 00:49:42,396
It's okay.

1122
00:49:42,479 --> 00:49:44,523
- Why are you bedridden?
- He's bedridden.

1123
00:49:44,606 --> 00:49:45,649
He's all slumped.

1124
00:49:45,732 --> 00:49:48,527
It's just an unfortunate situation because
it's perfect for a misunderstanding.

1125
00:49:48,610 --> 00:49:51,113
- Right. I hate those!
- The damage is done.

1126
00:49:51,196 --> 00:49:53,031
Kim Soo-hyun's
totally heartbroken right now.

1127
00:49:53,115 --> 00:49:56,284
She's probably thinking it would
have been better not to come, seriously.

1128
00:49:58,286 --> 00:50:00,789
- It feels good to get that out. Ah.
- Really?

1129
00:50:00,872 --> 00:50:03,375
- So you feel better now?
- Good to hear.

1130
00:50:03,458 --> 00:50:06,461
You see, I was uncomfortable,
because I thought it was on purpose.

1131
00:50:06,545 --> 00:50:08,755
See? It's good to clear up
these misunderstandings.

1132
00:50:08,839 --> 00:50:12,426
I have enough on my plate thinking
about my own things, so, it's kind of…

1133
00:50:12,509 --> 00:50:13,719
Right? Mm-hmm, sure, sure.

1134
00:50:14,553 --> 00:50:16,179
- Sure, sure.
- "Sure, sure."

1135
00:50:16,263 --> 00:50:17,347
I got it.

1136
00:50:18,098 --> 00:50:20,392
- Just take a breather.
- Huh?

1137
00:50:20,475 --> 00:50:21,643
"Take a breather"?

1138
00:50:21,727 --> 00:50:24,146
You're a really good friend. Thank you.

1139
00:50:26,732 --> 00:50:29,317
During that date,
I didn't feel any romantic attraction

1140
00:50:29,401 --> 00:50:31,778
to him at all, to be honest.

1141
00:50:31,862 --> 00:50:34,698
I seriously didn't feel a thing at all.
Not one bit.

1142
00:50:34,781 --> 00:50:37,492
Maybe Tae-hoon also said,
"Take a breather here,"

1143
00:50:37,576 --> 00:50:39,244
because he also felt comfortable
around her.

1144
00:50:41,538 --> 00:50:43,081
Then hurry up
and say something to Soo-hyun.

1145
00:50:43,165 --> 00:50:45,000
- Talk to Soo-hyun.
- Talk to her. Come on.

1146
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:48,462
- Don't you have any more questions for us?
- We'll tell you everything.

1147
00:50:48,545 --> 00:50:51,381
Honestly, you might not get another chance
if you don't do it now.

1148
00:50:51,465 --> 00:50:52,758
We're busy women, after all.

1149
00:50:52,841 --> 00:50:55,135
- Hurry 'cause our time is precious.
- How could you? Seriously.

1150
00:50:55,218 --> 00:50:59,097
- Hey! We're super popular people, okay?
- Hey! Busy, huh?

1151
00:50:59,181 --> 00:51:00,682
- Take a breather.
- What?

1152
00:51:01,391 --> 00:51:02,934
- Oh, no.
- He's doing it again!

1153
00:51:03,018 --> 00:51:04,436
So ridiculous.

1154
00:51:04,519 --> 00:51:07,147
- Take a breather.
- You're such a kind person.

1155
00:51:07,230 --> 00:51:08,857
But seriously, you can talk more.

1156
00:51:08,940 --> 00:51:11,068
- Uh, yeah. You aren't talking enough.
- I'm good.

1157
00:51:11,151 --> 00:51:13,070
- Yesterday…
- We barely know anything about you.

1158
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:15,947
Barely any information.
Please feel free to talk more. I mean it.

1159
00:51:16,031 --> 00:51:17,449
Take a breather here. Let's…

1160
00:51:17,532 --> 00:51:19,076
He even told Soo-hyun to take a breather.

1161
00:51:19,159 --> 00:51:21,203
- We're just really pressed for time.
- Right.

1162
00:51:21,286 --> 00:51:23,622
- Just relax, just relax.
- Woof.

1163
00:51:23,705 --> 00:51:26,291
- Oh, man.
- It's like the five sisters-in-law again.

1164
00:51:26,374 --> 00:51:27,918
Tae-hoon, this doesn't make you look cool.

1165
00:51:28,001 --> 00:51:29,044
You may think you look cool,

1166
00:51:29,127 --> 00:51:31,588
but you would actually look cool
if you were honest with them.

1167
00:51:31,671 --> 00:51:36,134
I feel Soo-hyun's also gonna be turned off
by that kind of behavior.

1168
00:51:36,218 --> 00:51:39,346
He's saying, "Just take a breather and go.
I'm not interested in you guys."

1169
00:51:39,429 --> 00:51:41,848
- Exactly. Like, "You should go."
- Such a wasted opportunity.

1170
00:51:44,309 --> 00:51:46,937
It appeared to me that the two of them
were taking this date

1171
00:51:47,020 --> 00:51:48,688
entirely too seriously,

1172
00:51:48,772 --> 00:51:51,316
so I just said that
to take the pressure off of them.

1173
00:51:53,026 --> 00:51:54,444
I actually liked that about him.

1174
00:51:54,528 --> 00:51:56,947
- Oh?
- Really?

1175
00:51:57,030 --> 00:51:58,907
- I guess he nailed it.
- That actually worked?

1176
00:51:58,990 --> 00:52:00,158
- That actually worked?
- Wait…

1177
00:52:00,242 --> 00:52:01,827
Well, I guess that's one way to do it.

1178
00:52:01,910 --> 00:52:02,911
But why?

1179
00:52:02,994 --> 00:52:05,580
Shh, just go along with it.
Don't say a word.

1180
00:52:05,664 --> 00:52:08,375
He lightened up the mood, and it was fun.

1181
00:52:09,876 --> 00:52:13,255
So I think that actually helped me
relax and enjoy the date.

1182
00:52:13,338 --> 00:52:14,840
- You watch baseball?
- I do, yes.

1183
00:52:14,923 --> 00:52:17,384
Yesterday, we talked about baseball
while drinking smoothies,

1184
00:52:17,467 --> 00:52:20,595
and today's conversation went well too,
so I was in a good mood.

1185
00:52:20,679 --> 00:52:21,680
I ate this.

1186
00:52:22,347 --> 00:52:25,100
I think my feelings for Tae-hoon
grew even more.

1187
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:28,019
Tae-hoon's impressive.

1188
00:52:28,103 --> 00:52:29,396
- What a legend.
- They really click.

1189
00:52:29,479 --> 00:52:31,273
- Tae-hoon's the best.
- Oh, wow, wow.

1190
00:52:31,356 --> 00:52:33,817
I'm not sure what his plan was,
but it worked.

1191
00:52:33,900 --> 00:52:35,318
She liked it, that's all that matters!

1192
00:52:35,402 --> 00:52:37,195
- Who cares about our opinions?
- Exactly.

1193
00:52:37,279 --> 00:52:39,030
- You got this.
- Hey, this is great.

1194
00:52:39,114 --> 00:52:40,448
Whatever works, right?

1195
00:52:40,532 --> 00:52:43,451
SEUNG-HYUN'S THREE-WAY DATE

1196
00:52:45,453 --> 00:52:47,164
- Oh, he doesn't look well.
- Seung-hyun.

1197
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:49,249
Seung-hyun looks like a nervous wreck.

1198
00:52:49,332 --> 00:52:50,959
Seung-hyun, are you okay?

1199
00:52:51,042 --> 00:52:53,461
Wow, why is he so nervous?

1200
00:52:55,255 --> 00:52:57,215
- Oh! Hello.
- Hello.

1201
00:52:57,299 --> 00:52:58,884
- Su-ji sure is busy.
- She's busy.

1202
00:52:58,967 --> 00:52:59,968
SU-JI
SEUNG-HYUN'S TOP PICK

1203
00:53:00,051 --> 00:53:02,012
- Oh, sit…
- Hello.

1204
00:53:03,805 --> 00:53:06,183
I was expecting it,
because the day before, he told me,

1205
00:53:06,266 --> 00:53:08,268
"I think you're my top pick now,

1206
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:10,562
and I don't think that's going
to change any time soon."

1207
00:53:10,645 --> 00:53:13,190
So I had somewhat seen this coming today.

1208
00:53:13,273 --> 00:53:15,400
- This is… ooh, that looks good.
- Oh.

1209
00:53:15,483 --> 00:53:18,069
I had a brief conversation
with Su-ji yesterday evening,

1210
00:53:18,153 --> 00:53:20,113
so I thought I should talk to her
about it some more,

1211
00:53:20,197 --> 00:53:21,740
try to express my feelings,

1212
00:53:21,823 --> 00:53:24,993
and actively engage her
in more conversation.

1213
00:53:25,076 --> 00:53:26,286
When did you get here?

1214
00:53:26,369 --> 00:53:27,537
- I just got here.
- Just now?

1215
00:53:27,621 --> 00:53:29,080
Just like you. It was a little far, right?

1216
00:53:29,164 --> 00:53:30,081
Right, right.

1217
00:53:30,874 --> 00:53:33,460
- It's day five now, as you know.
- Mm-hmm.

1218
00:53:33,543 --> 00:53:35,128
Time sure flies, doesn't it?

1219
00:53:35,212 --> 00:53:36,713
- Totally.
- I feel like it's going too fast.

1220
00:53:36,796 --> 00:53:39,216
- We don't really have much time left.
- Right. I mean…

1221
00:53:39,299 --> 00:53:43,970
Between yesterday and today,
things have changed so much for everyone.

1222
00:53:44,054 --> 00:53:49,684
In particular, I feel like the guys
are suddenly being super proactive.

1223
00:53:49,768 --> 00:53:51,394
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

1224
00:53:51,478 --> 00:53:53,021
Have you guys been talking a lot?

1225
00:53:53,688 --> 00:53:56,483
All the girls thought,
"They must have talked it over."

1226
00:53:56,566 --> 00:53:57,776
- Oh, really?
- Mm-hmm.

1227
00:53:58,944 --> 00:54:00,111
By the way…

1228
00:54:00,904 --> 00:54:02,948
you said you were confused yesterday.

1229
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:04,115
Right.

1230
00:54:04,199 --> 00:54:07,953
Has that… changed at all on your part?

1231
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:18,630
I don't really have anything
right now, so--

1232
00:54:18,713 --> 00:54:21,716
- Oh, you haven't figured it out yet?
- No, it's still the same.

1233
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:23,009
- The same?
- Yes, the same.

1234
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:24,135
It hasn't changed?

1235
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:29,224
Hmm, but to be honest,

1236
00:54:29,724 --> 00:54:32,102
I told you that I couldn't
give you an answer

1237
00:54:32,185 --> 00:54:35,897
because my feelings for you
were in flux, remember?

1238
00:54:35,981 --> 00:54:39,067
I could tell you that I might
develop feelings for you in the future,

1239
00:54:39,150 --> 00:54:40,902
but that may never happen.

1240
00:54:40,986 --> 00:54:42,028
Oh, right, that's true.

1241
00:54:42,112 --> 00:54:44,990
I could also end up falling for you
despite having said the opposite.

1242
00:54:46,116 --> 00:54:48,618
So in the current situation,
we can't really put a label on--

1243
00:54:48,702 --> 00:54:51,997
For now, I think it's too soon for me…

1244
00:54:52,080 --> 00:54:52,914
Ah. Mm-hmm.

1245
00:54:52,998 --> 00:54:55,750
…to tell you whether things
will or won't work out between us.

1246
00:54:55,834 --> 00:54:56,876
Ah, okay.

1247
00:54:58,378 --> 00:55:00,297
I was just a little confused.

1248
00:55:00,380 --> 00:55:04,426
I was confused as to whether
I had a chance at all in her eyes,

1249
00:55:04,509 --> 00:55:08,805
or if her intentions were simply
to come to the date and just talk to me.

1250
00:55:08,888 --> 00:55:10,056
She wasn't being specific.

1251
00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:12,600
I thought it would be nice
if she elaborated,

1252
00:55:12,684 --> 00:55:15,186
but since she didn't do that,
it was really…

1253
00:55:16,104 --> 00:55:20,525
I was just unsure
of how to take it, really.

1254
00:55:24,446 --> 00:55:26,573
Oh, somebody's coming.

1255
00:55:28,700 --> 00:55:30,827
- Again? Soo-hyun.
- Soo-hyun?

1256
00:55:30,910 --> 00:55:32,662
- Oh, my…
- Well, well, well.

1257
00:55:32,746 --> 00:55:34,331
- Hello.
- Hello there.

1258
00:55:36,750 --> 00:55:38,084
- Hello.
- Wow. Hello.

1259
00:55:38,168 --> 00:55:40,712
I hadn't expected
Seung-hyun to pick me at all,

1260
00:55:40,795 --> 00:55:44,174
so that's why I mostly thought,
"Huh? What's this? Why me?"

1261
00:55:44,257 --> 00:55:46,259
I wasn't sure what was happening.

1262
00:55:46,343 --> 00:55:49,054
I picked Soo-hyun
in the first impression vote, right?

1263
00:55:49,137 --> 00:55:52,015
And since I had enjoyed
my date with her yesterday…

1264
00:55:52,098 --> 00:55:54,476
- What even is this?
- Oh, wow, so they did all that stuff.

1265
00:55:55,226 --> 00:55:56,811
Don't you have any questions for us?

1266
00:55:56,895 --> 00:55:58,480
There must be a reason you summoned us.

1267
00:55:58,563 --> 00:56:00,440
There must be a reason. Go ahead.

1268
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:02,817
- Ask us or interview us.
- Ask us some questions.

1269
00:56:04,611 --> 00:56:07,155
- Then I do have a question for you.
- Mmm.

1270
00:56:07,989 --> 00:56:10,867
Did you guys, by chance,
check the Post Office?

1271
00:56:10,950 --> 00:56:12,577
Oh, I didn't go today.

1272
00:56:12,660 --> 00:56:14,245
The last time I went
was yesterday evening.

1273
00:56:14,329 --> 00:56:15,413
Ah, you didn't go today?

1274
00:56:15,497 --> 00:56:17,791
- No. We didn't have time to go.
- Oh, really?

1275
00:56:17,874 --> 00:56:19,250
- You went?
- I went.

1276
00:56:19,334 --> 00:56:20,919
- Oh, really?
- This morning?

1277
00:56:21,002 --> 00:56:22,170
It's a secret.

1278
00:56:24,839 --> 00:56:25,965
Okay. What else?

1279
00:56:26,049 --> 00:56:28,009
- Next…
- Next question. Dun dun dun.

1280
00:56:28,093 --> 00:56:30,011
Next question?
Ah, this is so difficult, though.

1281
00:56:30,095 --> 00:56:31,721
- Really? Think hard.
- It's a bit…

1282
00:56:31,805 --> 00:56:34,224
What are you doing
with two beautiful women here?

1283
00:56:34,307 --> 00:56:36,059
Oh, I know.

1284
00:56:36,142 --> 00:56:38,186
It's like I'm an interviewer.
This is so difficult.

1285
00:56:38,269 --> 00:56:40,146
Seems like there isn't anything
he wants to know.

1286
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:41,606
That's not what it is.

1287
00:56:41,689 --> 00:56:44,692
- Oh, dear. We should leave.
- No, no. It's not that.

1288
00:56:44,776 --> 00:56:47,070
At least on this date,
they're teasing Seung-hyun.

1289
00:56:49,739 --> 00:56:51,950
- No, no.
- Why not? Just do it.

1290
00:56:52,033 --> 00:56:53,243
- It's not…
- Guess it's a secret.

1291
00:56:53,326 --> 00:56:55,829
It's not a secret. I was going to ask
some lighthearted questions,

1292
00:56:55,912 --> 00:56:57,205
but I'm not sure it's a good idea.

1293
00:56:57,288 --> 00:56:58,206
Lighthearted question?

1294
00:56:58,289 --> 00:57:00,708
I was just going to ask if you liked
vinyl records and stuff,

1295
00:57:00,792 --> 00:57:02,710
since this place gives off
that sort of vibe.

1296
00:57:02,794 --> 00:57:04,712
- Oh, I'm not that into vinyl.
- Oh, really?

1297
00:57:04,796 --> 00:57:08,299
No, me neither. Seeing one and going,
"Wow, that's pretty," only lasts so long.

1298
00:57:08,383 --> 00:57:09,551
He must be so nervous.

1299
00:57:09,634 --> 00:57:11,928
I didn't exactly enjoy myself, no.

1300
00:57:12,011 --> 00:57:14,848
I had to kind of play the host
and keep the conversation going

1301
00:57:14,931 --> 00:57:18,309
with the two of them,
which was rather difficult and awkward.

1302
00:57:20,019 --> 00:57:22,730
It's not often that you come across
a blind date scene

1303
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:24,691
that makes you watch it like this.

1304
00:57:24,774 --> 00:57:27,235
- Yes.
- It doesn't happen very often.

1305
00:57:27,318 --> 00:57:29,904
Car, the Garden watched it
with that exact look in his eyes.

1306
00:57:29,988 --> 00:57:31,448
He was so annoyed throughout.

1307
00:57:31,531 --> 00:57:33,241
We're already on the second season
of this show,

1308
00:57:33,324 --> 00:57:34,701
but I still can't get used to it.

1309
00:57:36,369 --> 00:57:37,912
Man, this is pretty difficult.

1310
00:57:37,996 --> 00:57:39,622
So frustrating, man.

1311
00:57:39,706 --> 00:57:41,499
I mean, I get that he was nervous,

1312
00:57:41,583 --> 00:57:43,460
but it was honestly
too soon to ask her today

1313
00:57:43,543 --> 00:57:44,919
for an answer to yesterday's question.

1314
00:57:45,003 --> 00:57:46,337
He definitely jumped the gun.

1315
00:57:46,421 --> 00:57:48,047
- Too soon.
- He jumped the gun.

1316
00:57:49,966 --> 00:57:51,050
Who is it?

1317
00:57:51,134 --> 00:57:52,677
- It's Hyuk-joon.
- Hyuk-joon!

1318
00:57:52,760 --> 00:57:54,929
I'm curious about Hyuk-joon's
true intentions.

1319
00:57:57,682 --> 00:58:00,768
Who could be coming through the door?

1320
00:58:01,978 --> 00:58:03,188
Is it Hyun-seo?

1321
00:58:04,939 --> 00:58:06,232
It has to be Hyun-seo.

1322
00:58:06,316 --> 00:58:08,026
She has to come.

1323
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:10,820
- Hello.
- Hello.

1324
00:58:13,031 --> 00:58:14,741
- Oh!
- It's Han-ju.

1325
00:58:14,824 --> 00:58:16,326
- Hello.
- Hello.

1326
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:20,246
- Where should I sit?
- Wherever you want.

1327
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:23,875
HAN-JU
HYUK-JOON'S SECOND PICK

1328
00:58:24,626 --> 00:58:26,252
I didn't think you'd ask to see me.

1329
00:58:26,336 --> 00:58:27,629
- You didn't?
- No.

1330
00:58:27,712 --> 00:58:29,047
- You had no idea?
- Nope.

1331
00:58:30,548 --> 00:58:33,801
I chose Han-ju
because I liked her vibes yesterday

1332
00:58:33,885 --> 00:58:36,638
when we were talking
on her three-way date.

1333
00:58:38,389 --> 00:58:40,266
- Are you feeling better?
- Uh-huh. I'm better now.

1334
00:58:40,350 --> 00:58:42,143
So they were each other's second choice.

1335
00:58:42,227 --> 00:58:43,061
I guess so.

1336
00:58:43,144 --> 00:58:46,648
Honestly, I'd thought I wouldn't
even be able to get out of the dorm,

1337
00:58:46,731 --> 00:58:49,025
so I was grateful he asked for me.

1338
00:58:49,651 --> 00:58:52,654
- I'm happy for you, Han-ju.
- Ah, that's a relief.

1339
00:58:54,656 --> 00:58:56,741
I heard you got really drunk last night.

1340
00:58:56,824 --> 00:58:57,951
Uh-huh.

1341
00:58:58,743 --> 00:59:00,245
Were you feeling down yesterday?

1342
00:59:00,912 --> 00:59:02,038
I was a little…

1343
00:59:02,997 --> 00:59:04,999
I was a little troubled after the date.

1344
00:59:05,667 --> 00:59:09,128
Everyone, everyone was a bit that way,
so maybe it rubbed off on me.

1345
00:59:12,799 --> 00:59:15,301
Can you tell me honestly
why you were troubled?

1346
00:59:16,636 --> 00:59:17,845
Uh…

1347
00:59:20,974 --> 00:59:24,727
Well, I would say that other women
were also very interested

1348
00:59:24,811 --> 00:59:27,647
in the people I chose
as my top and second picks,

1349
00:59:28,356 --> 00:59:30,233
so that bothered me.

1350
00:59:31,276 --> 00:59:33,528
Lots of things like that.

1351
00:59:35,697 --> 00:59:38,825
I just had a lot of things on my mind.

1352
00:59:38,908 --> 00:59:43,288
And given that I was kind of stressed out
over finding Jin-woo's diary,

1353
00:59:43,371 --> 00:59:45,999
it made it hard for me
to focus on the date.

1354
00:59:47,125 --> 00:59:50,628
I wasn't really disappointed
in Hyuk-joon or anything like that,

1355
00:59:50,712 --> 00:59:54,424
but because I'm feeling
really quite discouraged right now,

1356
00:59:54,507 --> 00:59:57,176
it's hard to expect a lot from him
on this date.

1357
00:59:57,677 --> 00:59:59,804
I think reading Jin-woo's diary
hit her hard.

1358
00:59:59,887 --> 01:00:02,348
The fact that her name
wasn't mentioned once.

1359
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:06,185
Ah, this is an important opportunity,
but I don't know what to say.

1360
01:00:14,819 --> 01:00:17,363
- Hello.
- Hello.

1361
01:00:18,031 --> 01:00:19,282
HYUN-SEO
HYUK-JOON'S TOP PICK

1362
01:00:19,365 --> 01:00:20,742
- Hello.
- Hello.

1363
01:00:21,242 --> 01:00:23,369
- Hello.
- Oh, her outfit today's kind of wow.

1364
01:00:23,453 --> 01:00:24,954
Like someone who might say, "Who am I?

1365
01:00:25,038 --> 01:00:26,706
- I'm classy, look at me."
- You're right.

1366
01:00:26,789 --> 01:00:29,292
- I'm getting, "So it was you?" vibes.
- That was the vibes I got.

1367
01:00:29,375 --> 01:00:30,835
Do I sit here?

1368
01:00:36,090 --> 01:00:38,217
Thank you for joining me on my show.

1369
01:00:38,301 --> 01:00:40,011
- Oh, thank you for having me.
- Right.

1370
01:00:41,054 --> 01:00:42,055
Mmm.

1371
01:00:44,932 --> 01:00:46,434
Han-ju was there.

1372
01:00:47,977 --> 01:00:49,979
I thought, "My roommate is here."

1373
01:00:50,063 --> 01:00:51,898
I think I was really wary of her.

1374
01:00:52,732 --> 01:00:56,944
I knew that Hyuk-joon
was Han-ju's second pick yesterday,

1375
01:00:57,487 --> 01:00:59,322
so I was rather worried.

1376
01:01:00,573 --> 01:01:01,908
Let me set this up for you.

1377
01:01:04,202 --> 01:01:05,203
Ooh…

1378
01:01:05,745 --> 01:01:06,954
- Is that salt?
- What is this?

1379
01:01:07,038 --> 01:01:08,331
It's sand.

1380
01:01:09,957 --> 01:01:13,878
Today, you'll be making a product
called a "Gel Oil Lamp."

1381
01:01:13,961 --> 01:01:15,838
You could create one for yourself,

1382
01:01:15,922 --> 01:01:20,343
but we also get many guests
creating them as a gift for one another.

1383
01:01:20,426 --> 01:01:22,220
Let me know when you want to pour the gel.

1384
01:01:22,303 --> 01:01:23,429
Okay. Thank you.

1385
01:01:23,513 --> 01:01:24,722
Thank you.

1386
01:01:29,602 --> 01:01:31,396
I love the way it sounds.

1387
01:01:31,479 --> 01:01:34,315
- Ooh, ASMR.
- Totally.

1388
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:37,568
You said you were an outdoorsy person.
What do you usually do?

1389
01:01:37,652 --> 01:01:41,489
For starters, I love going
to exhibitions and movies,

1390
01:01:42,323 --> 01:01:44,242
and, well, concerts,
as I mentioned last time.

1391
01:01:44,325 --> 01:01:45,410
Right, right.

1392
01:01:45,493 --> 01:01:47,829
- And, well, going for drives.
- Mmm.

1393
01:01:47,912 --> 01:01:50,123
Where do you usually go
for a drive in Seoul?

1394
01:01:50,206 --> 01:01:52,542
In Seoul, I usually go to the outskirts.

1395
01:01:52,625 --> 01:01:53,918
Oh…

1396
01:01:54,001 --> 01:01:56,170
- IKEA's fun.
- I think so.

1397
01:01:56,254 --> 01:01:59,382
There's a lot to eat,
and the different areas are fun.

1398
01:01:59,465 --> 01:02:00,466
Mmm.

1399
01:02:02,385 --> 01:02:03,386
Have you been there?

1400
01:02:03,469 --> 01:02:05,012
- "Ike"?
- IKEA.

1401
01:02:06,055 --> 01:02:08,933
It's a store where they sell furniture,
but furniture isn't--

1402
01:02:09,016 --> 01:02:10,643
So you go for a drive to IKEA?

1403
01:02:10,727 --> 01:02:12,895
- Uh-huh, IKEA…
- Since it's on the outskirts.

1404
01:02:12,979 --> 01:02:14,188
Uh-huh, uh-huh.

1405
01:02:14,272 --> 01:02:17,191
- Was Hyun-seo a homebody?
- She is a little, yeah.

1406
01:02:17,275 --> 01:02:18,484
It kinda shows.

1407
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:21,487
You guys, are there
any travel destinations

1408
01:02:21,571 --> 01:02:23,197
that you've enjoyed in particular?

1409
01:02:24,365 --> 01:02:28,327
Travel? Well, to be honest,
I'm not really into traveling.

1410
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:30,997
When I went on trips
it wasn't because I wanted to,

1411
01:02:31,080 --> 01:02:33,708
but rather because my family
asked me to come with them.

1412
01:02:34,417 --> 01:02:36,335
I'd just go along with them.

1413
01:02:36,419 --> 01:02:38,171
Oh, so you just go along with it?

1414
01:02:38,254 --> 01:02:41,716
I'm not really interested
in tourist attractions.

1415
01:02:42,842 --> 01:02:46,095
I don't particularly feel the urge
to experience them,

1416
01:02:46,179 --> 01:02:48,473
so I'll go along
when someone says, "Let's go."

1417
01:02:48,556 --> 01:02:49,807
Ooh…

1418
01:02:51,601 --> 01:02:55,438
As for me, uh, purely in terms of fun,
I like Shanghai.

1419
01:02:55,521 --> 01:02:57,356
Oh, when did you go to Shanghai?

1420
01:02:57,440 --> 01:02:59,317
About a year ago, in the fall.

1421
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:01,152
Oh, right when it was up
seeing a boom in tourism.

1422
01:03:01,235 --> 01:03:03,571
It kind of had a European vibe,

1423
01:03:03,654 --> 01:03:05,323
but since it was in China,

1424
01:03:05,406 --> 01:03:08,534
well, the food was good and all,
so it was memorable for me.

1425
01:03:09,160 --> 01:03:12,747
I had a rough time in Europe,
but I've come to see it more positively.

1426
01:03:13,456 --> 01:03:14,916
So I think I enjoyed it.

1427
01:03:16,000 --> 01:03:17,168
Oh, they're clicking.

1428
01:03:18,002 --> 01:03:19,629
They get along well.

1429
01:03:20,797 --> 01:03:23,257
I wonder what you guys will have in mind
when you make those.

1430
01:03:23,341 --> 01:03:25,134
Wherever my flow of consciousness
takes me.

1431
01:03:25,218 --> 01:03:26,928
Oh, the flow of your consciousness?

1432
01:03:27,845 --> 01:03:29,597
- It isn't easy.
- Yeah, I know.

1433
01:03:29,680 --> 01:03:32,099
I want to put this starfish
on top of this octopus, but…

1434
01:03:32,183 --> 01:03:34,060
Help her, Hyuk-joon, help her.

1435
01:03:34,143 --> 01:03:36,771
Oh, hold on. This is kind of bothering me.

1436
01:03:40,817 --> 01:03:43,319
- It's precious.
- It's cute.

1437
01:03:43,986 --> 01:03:45,238
Thank you.

1438
01:03:46,155 --> 01:03:48,115
- Ooh, that's bad.
- Are you okay?

1439
01:03:54,956 --> 01:03:58,960
There's nothing special about this scene,
so why is it making me so nervous?

1440
01:04:00,962 --> 01:04:04,507
It wasn't the most
enjoyable time, actually.

1441
01:04:04,590 --> 01:04:07,343
Hyuk-joon took really good care of Han-ju.

1442
01:04:08,344 --> 01:04:12,223
And in my eyes, it seemed
as though he was trying really hard

1443
01:04:12,306 --> 01:04:14,559
to make us feel
he was treating us equally.

1444
01:04:15,309 --> 01:04:17,353
When it was just the two of us,

1445
01:04:17,436 --> 01:04:20,106
he made it seem like
he had strong feelings for me.

1446
01:04:20,606 --> 01:04:23,651
To be honest, I picked you
for the first impression vote.

1447
01:04:24,193 --> 01:04:25,403
Oh, really?

1448
01:04:25,486 --> 01:04:27,029
But I also like your voice so much.

1449
01:04:27,113 --> 01:04:28,281
Oh…

1450
01:04:28,364 --> 01:04:30,241
They say fate is a series of coincidences…

1451
01:04:30,324 --> 01:04:32,618
- Right, right, right.
- …that happen to coincide.

1452
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:34,996
- The thing is, this is kind of like fate.
- Fate?

1453
01:04:35,746 --> 01:04:37,707
But when others are around,

1454
01:04:37,790 --> 01:04:40,877
he doesn't really act
as though he's that into me.

1455
01:04:41,627 --> 01:04:43,713
I have a very defensive personality,

1456
01:04:43,796 --> 01:04:46,007
and I don't really show my feelings,

1457
01:04:46,090 --> 01:04:48,009
so this time, I tried really hard

1458
01:04:48,092 --> 01:04:51,178
to make my feelings obvious
to the person I liked.

1459
01:04:52,013 --> 01:04:53,014
I'll pick you.

1460
01:04:53,681 --> 01:04:55,558
Where has that version of Hyuk-joon gone?

1461
01:04:55,641 --> 01:04:58,644
- You tried, Hyun-seo. We know.
- You made a lot of effort.

1462
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:02,607
I feel like I shouldn't
put myself out there too much by myself.

1463
01:05:03,816 --> 01:05:05,610
That's right.
Don't let the food go to waste.

1464
01:05:05,693 --> 01:05:07,904
I agree.

1465
01:05:09,864 --> 01:05:11,407
THE THREE-WAY DATE IS OVER

1466
01:05:11,490 --> 01:05:13,784
Oh, wow, it's 3:30.

1467
01:05:14,452 --> 01:05:16,120
Thanks, that was really fun.

1468
01:05:16,203 --> 01:05:17,914
- I had fun.
- I had a good time.

1469
01:05:18,456 --> 01:05:20,625
- See you later.
- Bye.

1470
01:05:20,708 --> 01:05:21,918
See you later.

1471
01:05:24,170 --> 01:05:25,379
Okay.

1472
01:05:34,555 --> 01:05:36,349
Many thoughts ran through my head.

1473
01:05:36,891 --> 01:05:39,018
Oh, I'm kind of lost.

1474
01:05:39,101 --> 01:05:40,770
I didn't know what had gotten into me.

1475
01:05:41,437 --> 01:05:44,315
I guess the feeling of disappointment
hit me hard.

1476
01:05:44,398 --> 01:05:48,486
I can actually pinpoint precisely
the part that disappointed me.

1477
01:05:48,569 --> 01:05:51,030
Are there any travel destinations
that you've enjoyed in particular?

1478
01:05:51,113 --> 01:05:54,283
To be honest,
I'm not really into traveling.

1479
01:05:54,367 --> 01:05:56,994
Hyun-seo started off
with what seemed to me

1480
01:05:57,078 --> 01:05:59,830
as a very negative response,
to all my hobbies,

1481
01:05:59,914 --> 01:06:02,416
which kind of bothered me.

1482
01:06:02,959 --> 01:06:05,378
Previously, she did the same
with the karaoke.

1483
01:06:05,461 --> 01:06:07,338
- No way I'm going there.
- I scored a 99.

1484
01:06:07,421 --> 01:06:08,714
- Whoa, for real?
- Uh-huh.

1485
01:06:08,798 --> 01:06:11,008
- I hate karaoke.
- I kinda like karaoke.

1486
01:06:11,092 --> 01:06:12,593
I'm not going in the Noraebang.

1487
01:06:12,677 --> 01:06:15,846
I like it when people talk
in a positive way and…

1488
01:06:15,930 --> 01:06:17,682
Do you like strolling by the Han River?

1489
01:06:17,765 --> 01:06:20,267
Honestly, there are way too many bugs
flying around there.

1490
01:06:20,351 --> 01:06:22,144
Oh, right, right.

1491
01:06:22,228 --> 01:06:24,939
- Yeah, I really hate flying insects.
- Oh, right, right.

1492
01:06:25,022 --> 01:06:27,650
I thought, "Why does
she keep expressing herself like this?"

1493
01:06:27,733 --> 01:06:29,068
She also said she hated karaoke,

1494
01:06:29,151 --> 01:06:31,612
and this time, she started off with,
"I don't like it."

1495
01:06:31,696 --> 01:06:32,947
It made me wonder,

1496
01:06:33,030 --> 01:06:35,741
"Is she saying she doesn't want
to do any of these things?"

1497
01:06:35,825 --> 01:06:37,910
I like positive people.

1498
01:06:37,994 --> 01:06:41,622
Han-ju, on the contrary,
just sounded positive.

1499
01:06:41,706 --> 01:06:46,335
This might sound funny,
but I felt like I was Han-ju's top pick.

1500
01:06:46,419 --> 01:06:50,172
And I also found I enjoyed
my conversations with her.

1501
01:06:51,424 --> 01:06:53,759
My attraction to my second choice
has increased.

1502
01:06:54,885 --> 01:06:56,595
Han-ju's top pick is Jin-woo, though.

1503
01:06:57,805 --> 01:07:00,307
Well, I get where Hyuk-joon
is coming from.

1504
01:07:00,391 --> 01:07:01,726
Yeah. And Hyun-seo too.

1505
01:07:01,809 --> 01:07:05,438
I think Hyuk-joon thinks
that if he and Hyun-seo

1506
01:07:05,521 --> 01:07:07,273
were to become a couple in the future,

1507
01:07:07,356 --> 01:07:09,316
there wouldn't be much
they could do together.

1508
01:07:09,400 --> 01:07:11,777
- He's always thinking about the future.
- Oh, that's right.

1509
01:07:11,861 --> 01:07:14,321
She's not against Hyuk-joon
asking her to do stuff with him.

1510
01:07:14,405 --> 01:07:16,240
She just doesn't like
going outside that much.

1511
01:07:16,323 --> 01:07:18,534
I totally get not liking doing things
that aren't efficient.

1512
01:07:18,617 --> 01:07:20,870
- Yes, I also get it, really.
- Mm-hmm, me too.

1513
01:07:20,953 --> 01:07:22,705
That's why they do seem
really incompatible.

1514
01:07:23,456 --> 01:07:24,832
But since Hyun-seo likes Hyuk-joon…

1515
01:07:24,915 --> 01:07:28,335
Right. And I can also see
where Hyun-seo's coming from.

1516
01:07:28,419 --> 01:07:31,088
When they're alone together,
Hyuk-joon treats her differently.

1517
01:07:31,172 --> 01:07:34,133
I think what Hyun-seo wants
is that Hyuk-joon should show her

1518
01:07:34,216 --> 01:07:35,968
that he likes her
when other people are around.

1519
01:07:36,052 --> 01:07:37,386
- Yes, that's right.
- Right, right.

1520
01:07:37,470 --> 01:07:38,596
It's Jae-seo.

1521
01:07:38,679 --> 01:07:40,473
He was the first one
to announce his plan for today.

1522
01:07:40,556 --> 01:07:41,432
"Relax and have fun."

1523
01:07:47,188 --> 01:07:48,939
Whoa, why does he look almost tearful?

1524
01:07:49,023 --> 01:07:50,232
Oh, he looks like a poet.

1525
01:07:56,405 --> 01:07:57,239
Hello.

1526
01:08:00,868 --> 01:08:02,495
Yes, please, sit wherever you'd like.

1527
01:08:03,871 --> 01:08:07,333
SEO-YOON
JAE-SEO'S TOP PICK

1528
01:08:07,416 --> 01:08:09,251
- This… This is a bit awkward.
- Uh-huh.

1529
01:08:09,335 --> 01:08:10,836
- But… But I brought them.
- Oh, really?

1530
01:08:10,920 --> 01:08:12,129
The cookies you mentioned earlier.

1531
01:08:13,464 --> 01:08:16,926
So, uh, I picked some cute ones
to bring here for us.

1532
01:08:17,009 --> 01:08:18,385
Oh.

1533
01:08:19,345 --> 01:08:21,388
- Shouldn't it be the other way around?
- Let's try them.

1534
01:08:21,472 --> 01:08:22,848
- Oh, really? How so?
- I thought…

1535
01:08:22,932 --> 01:08:25,851
"Shouldn't we save the cute ones
and eat the ugly ones?"

1536
01:08:25,935 --> 01:08:27,937
- They came in multiples of three…
- Uh-huh.

1537
01:08:28,020 --> 01:08:30,856
…so I thought they would be perfect
for this occasion.

1538
01:08:31,982 --> 01:08:34,193
These two really click
with this kind of stuff.

1539
01:08:34,276 --> 01:08:36,195
They both have engineering backgrounds.

1540
01:08:36,278 --> 01:08:38,572
He just took an arrow to the heart.
Jae-seo's like…

1541
01:08:38,656 --> 01:08:40,407
- "Ah, she's so amazing, ah!"
- "Ah!"

1542
01:08:40,491 --> 01:08:42,243
- "Multiples of three."
- "Ah!"

1543
01:08:42,326 --> 01:08:43,536
No, no.

1544
01:08:44,787 --> 01:08:48,499
When we went on the three-way dates
initiated by the women,

1545
01:08:48,582 --> 01:08:51,627
I saw that Seo-yoon
seemed to be struggling a lot.

1546
01:08:51,710 --> 01:08:53,879
So I thought I should help her loosen up.

1547
01:08:53,963 --> 01:08:56,048
I knew Seo-yoon liked snack foods,

1548
01:08:56,132 --> 01:09:00,136
and since I figured she would like stuff
with cute characters on them,

1549
01:09:00,219 --> 01:09:01,512
I picked those cookies.

1550
01:09:01,595 --> 01:09:05,266
I'm guessing my intentions
at least got through to her.

1551
01:09:05,349 --> 01:09:08,227
It's so sweet that Jae-seo's
looking out for Seo-yoon's feelings

1552
01:09:08,310 --> 01:09:09,562
when he's also in a lot of pain.

1553
01:09:09,645 --> 01:09:11,856
He's a very considerate man, it's true.

1554
01:09:15,192 --> 01:09:17,736
What do you normally do? Back in the dorm?

1555
01:09:17,820 --> 01:09:20,322
I like listening to people talk, actually.

1556
01:09:20,406 --> 01:09:22,825
So I mostly gravitate
towards large gatherings.

1557
01:09:22,908 --> 01:09:24,660
That way I tend to pick up
on this and that.

1558
01:09:24,743 --> 01:09:26,829
Oh, you hear lots
of different conversations?

1559
01:09:26,912 --> 01:09:28,747
- Well, me…
- Uh-huh.

1560
01:09:28,831 --> 01:09:31,167
I was under the impression
that I was pretty perceptive

1561
01:09:31,250 --> 01:09:32,626
back in the real world,

1562
01:09:32,710 --> 01:09:35,838
but I honestly have no idea
what's going on in here.

1563
01:09:35,921 --> 01:09:37,006
Oh…

1564
01:09:37,089 --> 01:09:39,675
So I keep thinking,
"God, am I a little thick?"

1565
01:09:39,758 --> 01:09:41,635
- So here's the thing.
- That's how I feel.

1566
01:09:41,719 --> 01:09:44,430
I don't know if everyone feels this way,
but the way I see you,

1567
01:09:44,513 --> 01:09:46,891
you're someone I can only gain access to
by talking to Soo-hyun.

1568
01:09:46,974 --> 01:09:48,142
- So…
- Oh, really?

1569
01:09:48,225 --> 01:09:50,311
Since you guys are always
going around together,

1570
01:09:50,394 --> 01:09:51,812
it got to the point where I thought,

1571
01:09:51,896 --> 01:09:54,064
do I need to approach Soo-hyun
to get her to fetch you for me?

1572
01:09:54,148 --> 01:09:55,357
Oh, love it.

1573
01:09:55,441 --> 01:09:58,319
I've had a lot of
one-on-one conversations.

1574
01:09:58,402 --> 01:09:59,695
- With the men, that is.
- In advance?

1575
01:09:59,778 --> 01:10:01,238
I should be talking to the women,

1576
01:10:01,322 --> 01:10:03,574
but I'm having
one-on-one conversations with the men.

1577
01:10:03,657 --> 01:10:06,035
But that's why I can see all the matchups.

1578
01:10:06,118 --> 01:10:08,204
Oh, because you've already
had a lot of one-on-ones?

1579
01:10:08,287 --> 01:10:09,496
Yes, quite a few of them.

1580
01:10:09,580 --> 01:10:12,041
This one might be the last one
for you today.

1581
01:10:13,167 --> 01:10:14,001
Me?

1582
01:10:14,084 --> 01:10:15,336
- Yes, maybe.
- Huh?

1583
01:10:16,462 --> 01:10:17,463
What?

1584
01:10:18,088 --> 01:10:21,383
Is he saying what I'm thinking?
"I'm the only man who picked you"?

1585
01:10:22,051 --> 01:10:24,261
God, someone needs to tell him
to put a sock in it.

1586
01:10:24,345 --> 01:10:26,805
This one might be the last one
for you today.

1587
01:10:28,182 --> 01:10:29,350
- Me?
- Uh-huh. Yes, maybe.

1588
01:10:29,433 --> 01:10:31,894
I also… I totally thought
that would be the case.

1589
01:10:31,977 --> 01:10:35,397
Yeah, I was kind of aware of it
to some extent.

1590
01:10:36,065 --> 01:10:37,316
So…

1591
01:10:37,399 --> 01:10:40,319
I think the smile
disappeared from my face.

1592
01:10:40,402 --> 01:10:43,322
Jae-seo told me that the date
I was on right there with him

1593
01:10:43,405 --> 01:10:45,658
would be the last one for me,

1594
01:10:46,408 --> 01:10:50,788
and I can admit him telling me
came as quite a shock to me,

1595
01:10:50,871 --> 01:10:55,376
so I couldn't hide my emotions at all
and I really struggled.

1596
01:10:55,459 --> 01:10:58,462
I didn't know if Seo-yoon was able
to handle her stress from yesterday,

1597
01:10:58,545 --> 01:11:01,006
and the fact that she may have been
on her last date today.

1598
01:11:01,090 --> 01:11:04,635
That was definitely
another potential vector for stress.

1599
01:11:04,718 --> 01:11:06,762
It's a bitter pill to swallow,

1600
01:11:06,845 --> 01:11:10,349
but I figured preparing her for the worst
might bring her some peace of mind.

1601
01:11:10,432 --> 01:11:14,061
So I told her that there was a good chance
her date with me was her only date today.

1602
01:11:14,770 --> 01:11:16,981
I'll give you a bitter pill to swallow.

1603
01:11:17,064 --> 01:11:18,691
Very bitter, huh?

1604
01:11:18,774 --> 01:11:20,401
Ugh, why…

1605
01:11:20,484 --> 01:11:22,486
Oh, that's such an offensive thing to say.

1606
01:11:22,569 --> 01:11:24,822
I don't know why she had to swallow
this bitter pill,

1607
01:11:24,905 --> 01:11:27,700
and why he thought he should
be the one to make her swallow it.

1608
01:11:27,783 --> 01:11:28,784
This outcome is so sad.

1609
01:11:28,867 --> 01:11:30,744
Jae-seo is thinking
only from his own perspective.

1610
01:11:30,828 --> 01:11:31,745
Yes, I know.

1611
01:11:31,829 --> 01:11:34,164
Is he the type that likes
giving people a heads up?

1612
01:11:34,248 --> 01:11:36,208
He likes to share information with people.

1613
01:11:36,292 --> 01:11:38,043
I'm sure we've heard it before.

1614
01:11:38,127 --> 01:11:40,379
- "I'm saying this for your own good."
- "For your own good."

1615
01:11:40,462 --> 01:11:42,548
But most of the time,
it's just all nonsense.

1616
01:11:42,631 --> 01:11:43,841
If the person didn't ask for it.

1617
01:11:43,924 --> 01:11:47,052
Besides, how do you possibly
say something like that

1618
01:11:47,136 --> 01:11:49,096
to a woman you're attracted to?

1619
01:11:50,014 --> 01:11:51,807
Her upset look is going to give her away.

1620
01:11:55,811 --> 01:11:57,187
- Hi, hi.
- Hello.

1621
01:11:57,271 --> 01:11:59,732
- Another woman to make it worse.
- This is uncomfortable.

1622
01:12:02,484 --> 01:12:03,736
HAN-JU
JAE-SEO'S SECOND PICK

1623
01:12:03,819 --> 01:12:05,654
So this is how it feels?

1624
01:12:05,738 --> 01:12:07,990
I didn't get to experience it yesterday,
so yeah.

1625
01:12:11,076 --> 01:12:13,537
- Check this out.
- What is it? Cookies?

1626
01:12:13,620 --> 01:12:16,623
Apparently, she picked this one
because they come as multiples of three.

1627
01:12:16,707 --> 01:12:18,167
That's… that's the one I brought.

1628
01:12:18,250 --> 01:12:20,002
- I can smell the engineering major.
- Right.

1629
01:12:20,085 --> 01:12:23,464
I mean, well, earlier, he told me
we should have them when we're together.

1630
01:12:24,256 --> 01:12:26,717
I mean, she was also talking
about DBs just the other day.

1631
01:12:26,800 --> 01:12:27,676
Ah, yesterday.

1632
01:12:27,760 --> 01:12:30,012
I found it funny that she used
that word so casually.

1633
01:12:30,679 --> 01:12:33,265
Mm-hmm, multiples of three.

1634
01:12:33,349 --> 01:12:35,768
Did you guys notice that
there are some cats over there?

1635
01:12:35,851 --> 01:12:37,519
- Oh, really? I didn't see them.
- That's right.

1636
01:12:37,603 --> 01:12:39,438
They have up to three cats here.

1637
01:12:41,398 --> 01:12:43,650
I think there are some clear merits
and demerits to cats.

1638
01:12:43,734 --> 01:12:45,736
They never come to you.

1639
01:12:45,819 --> 01:12:49,531
I hate when they play hard to get.
Both men and animals.

1640
01:12:49,615 --> 01:12:51,742
You must be speaking from experience.

1641
01:12:51,825 --> 01:12:54,119
There are a lot of people
who play hard to get.

1642
01:12:54,203 --> 01:12:57,456
You kind of had a hunch
that the guys would get their turn today

1643
01:12:57,539 --> 01:12:59,208
because of the dates yesterday.

1644
01:13:00,042 --> 01:13:02,378
So what were you going to talk about?

1645
01:13:02,461 --> 01:13:04,713
When the three… three of us got together?

1646
01:13:04,797 --> 01:13:06,840
When we got together?
To be honest, for me,

1647
01:13:06,924 --> 01:13:09,510
the other person was someone
I was comfortable with.

1648
01:13:09,593 --> 01:13:10,928
Not someone I was attracted to.

1649
01:13:11,011 --> 01:13:13,430
I should say there's a clear difference
between the two.

1650
01:13:13,514 --> 01:13:16,100
So I thought,
"When I'm with both of them together,

1651
01:13:16,183 --> 01:13:19,061
I'll just hang out with them
as we do in the lounge."

1652
01:13:19,144 --> 01:13:22,272
You never know, I could be missing out
on an opportunity right now.

1653
01:13:27,945 --> 01:13:31,907
But the both of you, I'm sure
have people that you like, right?

1654
01:13:31,990 --> 01:13:33,909
Do you think they'll ask to see you?

1655
01:13:36,286 --> 01:13:38,539
You might go on a couple more dates.

1656
01:13:40,416 --> 01:13:43,585
I can never tell these things
in normal circumstances.

1657
01:13:43,669 --> 01:13:44,962
Here, I'm totally in the dark.

1658
01:13:45,045 --> 01:13:46,630
- Oh, really?
- Absolutely.

1659
01:13:47,506 --> 01:13:49,425
You feel a bit detached
from all this, right?

1660
01:13:49,508 --> 01:13:51,718
- Yeah, I'm a bit detached from it.
- Yeah.

1661
01:13:55,013 --> 01:13:56,557
That bastard.

1662
01:13:56,640 --> 01:13:58,684
I'm sorry, but what gives you the right

1663
01:13:58,767 --> 01:14:02,020
to tell people how many dates,
or not, they'll be going on?

1664
01:14:02,104 --> 01:14:05,315
I get where he was coming from earlier,
he made a mistake.

1665
01:14:05,399 --> 01:14:09,319
But to bring it up again in the context
of comparing the two women is…

1666
01:14:09,945 --> 01:14:12,156
is a serious faux pas.
He made a huge mistake.

1667
01:14:12,239 --> 01:14:13,949
Jae-seo doesn't seem to know it's rude.

1668
01:14:14,032 --> 01:14:17,161
I guess he's simply thinking,
"I'm just giving you guys information."

1669
01:14:17,244 --> 01:14:18,370
Right.

1670
01:14:18,454 --> 01:14:20,414
You feel a bit detached
from all this, right?

1671
01:14:20,497 --> 01:14:22,666
- Yeah, I'm a bit detached from it.
- Yeah.

1672
01:14:22,749 --> 01:14:25,169
And here I thought
I was pretty quick on the uptake.

1673
01:14:26,378 --> 01:14:28,547
Yeah. Well, you just need to participate.

1674
01:14:29,173 --> 01:14:31,675
I've never shown my feelings
to anyone ever.

1675
01:14:31,758 --> 01:14:33,260
Oh…

1676
01:14:33,343 --> 01:14:37,222
I just kept my feelings to myself
and hoped that by some stroke of luck,

1677
01:14:37,306 --> 01:14:38,891
the guy would like me back.

1678
01:14:38,974 --> 01:14:41,393
- Oh, so you wait.
- Praying for it is about all I can do.

1679
01:14:41,477 --> 01:14:43,604
- It's kind of like pray-flirting.
- Oh, you're right.

1680
01:14:43,687 --> 01:14:45,355
"Please like me. Amen."

1681
01:14:46,273 --> 01:14:48,901
After my visit
to the 5 Minute Library earlier…

1682
01:14:49,693 --> 01:14:52,905
I mean, well, it's not like
I got rejected to my face,

1683
01:14:52,988 --> 01:14:57,951
but the thought
that I'm likely to get rejected…

1684
01:14:58,035 --> 01:15:00,037
I might not be cut out for this.

1685
01:15:08,253 --> 01:15:12,049
Man, I was definitely planning on having
a fun conversation and having a good time,

1686
01:15:12,132 --> 01:15:13,926
but with each topic that comes up…

1687
01:15:14,009 --> 01:15:16,220
We're not even talking about me.

1688
01:15:16,303 --> 01:15:19,306
We're talking about you guys,
but I'm feeling kind of, you know…

1689
01:15:20,057 --> 01:15:21,350
She looks so upset.

1690
01:15:23,393 --> 01:15:26,522
When setting up my date,
I aimed, as much as possible,

1691
01:15:27,272 --> 01:15:28,607
not to offend anyone.

1692
01:15:28,690 --> 01:15:31,985
And also, today,
I wanted to limit how much I spoke

1693
01:15:32,069 --> 01:15:35,030
compared to how much I listened
to what others had to say.

1694
01:15:35,113 --> 01:15:37,699
I think I was a pretty good listener.

1695
01:15:37,783 --> 01:15:40,911
- Wow.
- This is a bit, uh…

1696
01:15:40,994 --> 01:15:44,581
This is so frustrating.
He doesn't know how hurtful he is, right?

1697
01:15:44,665 --> 01:15:46,083
- I feel so bad about all this.
- Uh-huh.

1698
01:15:46,166 --> 01:15:49,211
So, for real, for Jae-seo, to be honest,

1699
01:15:49,294 --> 01:15:53,674
there's no telling how this will be edited
and broadcast, but…

1700
01:15:54,466 --> 01:15:56,677
um, that, uh, anyway…

1701
01:15:56,760 --> 01:15:58,887
Look at him rubbing his eyes.

1702
01:15:58,971 --> 01:16:01,139
Talk about this
is stressing him out as well.

1703
01:16:01,723 --> 01:16:03,308
He was crushing his eyes.

1704
01:16:03,392 --> 01:16:04,810
It's because I'm genuinely concerned.

1705
01:16:04,893 --> 01:16:06,228
- Oh, man.
- I'm concerned.

1706
01:16:06,311 --> 01:16:08,522
- They're still so inexperienced.
- Right.

1707
01:16:09,189 --> 01:16:12,317
When it comes to love,
they keep making mistakes,

1708
01:16:12,401 --> 01:16:14,236
trying to look out for others,

1709
01:16:14,820 --> 01:16:17,239
without realizing
the possible consequences.

1710
01:16:17,322 --> 01:16:19,575
"Seo-yoon's going to be alone
like me yesterday."

1711
01:16:19,658 --> 01:16:20,951
I know. You're right.

1712
01:16:21,034 --> 01:16:25,414
But the words he said to Seo-yoon to spare
her some of the pain only hurt her more.

1713
01:16:25,497 --> 01:16:29,376
My girl is Jeon Seo-yoon,
and your boy is Kim Jae-seo,

1714
01:16:29,459 --> 01:16:31,295
so why am I defending him?

1715
01:16:31,378 --> 01:16:34,214
That's precisely what you should be doing,
defending your boy.

1716
01:16:34,298 --> 01:16:36,550
Whatever happened to that,
Car, the Garden?

1717
01:16:36,633 --> 01:16:39,720
Who said he would support the cast
like they do on <i>Single's Inferno</i>?

1718
01:16:39,803 --> 01:16:41,513
I will. I will be supportive.

1719
01:16:42,931 --> 01:16:44,933
- Okay, so Kim Jae-seo…
- "I'll be supportive."

1720
01:16:45,017 --> 01:16:46,143
That's even more annoying.

1721
01:16:46,226 --> 01:16:48,103
- Kim Jae-seo right here…
- Yeah.

1722
01:16:48,186 --> 01:16:50,480
…he likes to share information.

1723
01:16:50,564 --> 01:16:51,982
Yeah.

1724
01:16:52,065 --> 01:16:56,069
The way he likes to share the information
he's privy to…

1725
01:16:57,195 --> 01:16:59,072
is the true mark of an intellectual.

1726
01:16:59,156 --> 01:17:01,617
- What even was that?
- Is that being supportive?

1727
01:17:01,700 --> 01:17:03,076
What even was that?

1728
01:17:03,160 --> 01:17:04,911
JIN-WOO'S THREE-WAY DATE

1729
01:17:04,995 --> 01:17:06,371
Jin-woo. Ah!

1730
01:17:06,955 --> 01:17:09,124
- He's a popular man.
- Mr. Do-or-die.

1731
01:17:10,709 --> 01:17:13,128
- Oh, his heart must be pounding.
- Oh…

1732
01:17:27,392 --> 01:17:29,269
An Jeong-eun came in first.

1733
01:17:29,353 --> 01:17:30,896
She had chosen me the day before

1734
01:17:30,979 --> 01:17:33,649
when the women were initiating
the three-way dates,

1735
01:17:33,732 --> 01:17:36,151
and since she was already
on the list of women

1736
01:17:36,234 --> 01:17:38,153
I'm interested in anyway,

1737
01:17:38,236 --> 01:17:40,906
I thought this would be
a good opportunity to talk to her.

1738
01:17:40,989 --> 01:17:42,741
It's great to converse with one another.

1739
01:17:42,824 --> 01:17:44,034
Mmm.

1740
01:17:46,161 --> 01:17:47,162
Hello.

1741
01:17:48,538 --> 01:17:50,040
Thank you for making the trek out here.

1742
01:17:50,123 --> 01:17:51,458
It wasn't a trek at all.

1743
01:17:59,883 --> 01:18:01,176
He must be nervous.

1744
01:18:01,802 --> 01:18:05,013
Huh? Jeong-eun also seems to be excited.

1745
01:18:05,097 --> 01:18:06,264
It's a little awkward.

1746
01:18:06,348 --> 01:18:07,516
- Right?
- Mm-hmm.

1747
01:18:08,600 --> 01:18:10,936
- It's a little hard to get my words out.
- A little hard?

1748
01:18:11,019 --> 01:18:13,563
So maybe now you know
how I felt yesterday.

1749
01:18:15,732 --> 01:18:17,484
I can relate to you so much right now.

1750
01:18:18,735 --> 01:18:22,572
So, yesterday,
when both of you were there,

1751
01:18:22,656 --> 01:18:26,159
although there was a separate conversation
we needed to have in private,

1752
01:18:26,243 --> 01:18:29,579
I couldn't bring it up
while there was another person here.

1753
01:18:30,997 --> 01:18:32,666
Hard to talk about
with someone else present.

1754
01:18:32,749 --> 01:18:33,750
Exactly. I couldn't do that.

1755
01:18:33,834 --> 01:18:35,168
- It was a bit…
- So…

1756
01:18:35,252 --> 01:18:39,923
Uh, I couldn't help but feel bad
about how yesterday's date went,

1757
01:18:40,006 --> 01:18:42,676
actually, thinking,
"Did I just waste his time?"

1758
01:18:42,759 --> 01:18:44,511
Oh, I didn't feel that way.

1759
01:18:44,594 --> 01:18:45,595
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1760
01:18:45,679 --> 01:18:48,598
When they said the top
and second picks would go,

1761
01:18:48,682 --> 01:18:50,934
- I was hoping I would get to go…
- Ah.

1762
01:18:51,017 --> 01:18:53,395
…and I did get to go
right after I had that thought,

1763
01:18:53,478 --> 01:18:57,691
so I was quite happy that I got
to confirm your feelings for me.

1764
01:19:00,944 --> 01:19:03,822
Did I tell you this
when we went to Sparks House?

1765
01:19:03,905 --> 01:19:06,825
That I hesitated between the person
I like, and the person who likes me?

1766
01:19:06,908 --> 01:19:08,243
I think I've made up my mind.

1767
01:19:08,326 --> 01:19:09,953
Oh, so you've made up your mind?

1768
01:19:10,036 --> 01:19:13,206
I think I'll have fewer regrets
if I go toward the person I like.

1769
01:19:13,290 --> 01:19:15,000
Oh, really? So your thoughts have changed.

1770
01:19:15,083 --> 01:19:16,293
Mm-hmm. I know.

1771
01:19:16,835 --> 01:19:20,297
I think yesterday's date
strengthened my resolve.

1772
01:19:20,380 --> 01:19:22,549
- Oh, my, oh my.
- Oh, butterflies.

1773
01:19:22,632 --> 01:19:23,800
I was happy.

1774
01:19:23,884 --> 01:19:26,386
I got the sense
that he was telling me all that

1775
01:19:26,470 --> 01:19:30,015
to give me some assurance,
so I was grateful.

1776
01:19:31,892 --> 01:19:32,809
Oh!

1777
01:19:32,893 --> 01:19:35,145
Oh, so it gave you butterflies? Oh, okay.

1778
01:19:41,193 --> 01:19:43,862
To be honest, when we were talking,
the questions there…

1779
01:19:43,945 --> 01:19:46,114
Oh, is this Su-ji's fourth date?

1780
01:19:46,198 --> 01:19:47,532
Ah…

1781
01:19:51,620 --> 01:19:53,163
Here comes the challenging part.

1782
01:19:55,373 --> 01:19:57,042
Talking in a group is so hard.

1783
01:19:58,752 --> 01:19:59,836
What should we talk about?

1784
01:20:01,838 --> 01:20:03,757
Oh, hello!

1785
01:20:03,840 --> 01:20:05,801
Did I interrupt you?

1786
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:08,970
I was really surprised.

1787
01:20:09,054 --> 01:20:12,349
To be honest, I didn't even think
that Jin-woo was interested in me

1788
01:20:12,432 --> 01:20:14,893
until he actually told me right then,

1789
01:20:14,976 --> 01:20:17,312
and I was even less aware
of his attraction to Su-ji.

1790
01:20:17,395 --> 01:20:19,439
- Here's our superstar.
- You can sit here.

1791
01:20:19,523 --> 01:20:20,941
SU-JI
JIN-WOO'S TOP PICK

1792
01:20:21,024 --> 01:20:23,068
This is surprising.
I wasn't expecting this.

1793
01:20:23,151 --> 01:20:24,486
Just like how I felt earlier.

1794
01:20:24,569 --> 01:20:26,029
JEONG-EUN
JIN-WOO'S SECOND PICK

1795
01:20:26,655 --> 01:20:29,115
- What were you guys talking about?
- We just…

1796
01:20:30,283 --> 01:20:31,451
Oh, it's a bit hot in here.

1797
01:20:31,535 --> 01:20:33,370
- Are you hot?
- It's because he's struggling.

1798
01:20:33,453 --> 01:20:34,746
You are wearing a thick jacket.

1799
01:20:36,498 --> 01:20:37,499
Maybe I'm nervous.

1800
01:20:37,582 --> 01:20:38,667
That could be it.

1801
01:20:38,750 --> 01:20:40,460
- You must be really nervous.
- Oh, yeah.

1802
01:20:42,921 --> 01:20:44,881
He's really nervous
now that Su-ji is here.

1803
01:20:44,965 --> 01:20:46,174
He can't even talk.

1804
01:20:47,425 --> 01:20:50,637
- I didn't know I'd be coming here.
- You didn't know?

1805
01:20:50,720 --> 01:20:52,347
- Oh, you didn't know?
- No, no.

1806
01:20:53,265 --> 01:20:54,808
- I see.
- Mm-hmm.

1807
01:20:57,435 --> 01:20:59,813
What do you mean, you didn't know?
Of course you knew, Su-ji.

1808
01:20:59,896 --> 01:21:01,940
I mean, she even saw his letter, right?

1809
01:21:03,066 --> 01:21:06,111
Do you think your feelings could change
if someone you're not that into

1810
01:21:06,194 --> 01:21:07,946
keeps expressing their feelings for you?

1811
01:21:10,991 --> 01:21:12,909
I don't think they would change that much.

1812
01:21:14,494 --> 01:21:17,789
I always just cut off anyone
I wasn't interested in.

1813
01:21:17,873 --> 01:21:19,624
I never even gave them a chance.

1814
01:21:24,462 --> 01:21:27,382
Then do you try to approach someone
you're interested in?

1815
01:21:28,592 --> 01:21:29,968
Hmm…

1816
01:21:30,969 --> 01:21:32,053
I…

1817
01:21:34,306 --> 01:21:37,309
I think I try to approach them
once I'm really sure.

1818
01:21:38,268 --> 01:21:40,437
She seems to be keeping her distance.

1819
01:21:46,067 --> 01:21:48,695
I don't feel any other way
than to consider Jin-woo

1820
01:21:48,778 --> 01:21:50,405
as no more than a friend to me,

1821
01:21:50,488 --> 01:21:53,825
so if the topic came up,
I was going to tell him that.

1822
01:21:53,909 --> 01:21:56,912
But on that date, it felt awkward
to suddenly bring it up

1823
01:21:56,995 --> 01:22:00,832
since I couldn't find the right moment,
and I didn't want to embarrass him,

1824
01:22:00,916 --> 01:22:02,500
so I held back from saying it.

1825
01:22:03,460 --> 01:22:05,670
Right, and Jeong-eun was there too.

1826
01:22:05,754 --> 01:22:06,880
Yeah.

1827
01:22:10,467 --> 01:22:14,012
Uh, Su-ji didn't mention at all
how I wrote her a letter

1828
01:22:14,095 --> 01:22:16,306
and also sent her the gloves as a gift.

1829
01:22:17,098 --> 01:22:20,393
She was staring into space
unless I talked to her, so I thought,

1830
01:22:20,477 --> 01:22:22,896
"Ah, she must not have
any feelings for me at all."

1831
01:22:22,979 --> 01:22:25,899
It made things super awkward
and a little uncomfortable.

1832
01:22:29,694 --> 01:22:31,321
She knows where to draw the line.

1833
01:22:31,404 --> 01:22:34,366
Su-ji told Jin-woo
that she wouldn't change her mind

1834
01:22:34,449 --> 01:22:36,576
for someone she wasn't interested in,

1835
01:22:36,660 --> 01:22:38,870
even if they expressed
their feelings for her.

1836
01:22:38,954 --> 01:22:41,039
- I'd say that was a clear rejection.
- Yes.

1837
01:22:41,122 --> 01:22:42,499
That way she sent him packing.

1838
01:22:42,582 --> 01:22:46,544
From Jin-woo's perspective, he could think
that he was rejected right away earlier

1839
01:22:46,628 --> 01:22:48,880
when he expressed his feelings for her
at the Post Office.

1840
01:22:48,964 --> 01:22:51,716
He could legitimately be a little hurt.

1841
01:22:51,800 --> 01:22:54,844
But then again, since Jin-woo
was Jeong-eun's second choice

1842
01:22:54,928 --> 01:22:58,306
and Jeong-eun is Jin-woo's second choice,
things might work out between them.

1843
01:22:58,390 --> 01:23:01,017
- You're right.
- Jeong-eun seems to be responding well.

1844
01:23:01,101 --> 01:23:02,477
Oh, thank goodness.

1845
01:23:02,560 --> 01:23:05,730
Jin Woo's date wraps up
the male singles' three-way dates,

1846
01:23:05,814 --> 01:23:08,400
and Su-ji went on a whopping four dates.

1847
01:23:08,483 --> 01:23:09,359
Wow.

1848
01:23:09,442 --> 01:23:11,778
And of those, the only one
she's dating mutually is Jung-yun.

1849
01:23:11,861 --> 01:23:13,279
Uh-huh, Jung-yun and Su-ji.

1850
01:23:13,363 --> 01:23:16,741
We thought Jung-yun was on thin ice
with the way he expressed himself earlier.

1851
01:23:16,825 --> 01:23:17,659
Yep.

1852
01:23:17,742 --> 01:23:20,370
- But it actually worked out for him.
- Su-ji actually liked it.

1853
01:23:20,453 --> 01:23:22,539
I'm happy as long
as both Soo-hyun and Su-ji like it.

1854
01:23:22,622 --> 01:23:23,707
Right, right.

1855
01:23:24,916 --> 01:23:26,668
Where did everyone go?

1856
01:23:26,751 --> 01:23:28,920
Is he back? He must be back from his date.

1857
01:23:29,671 --> 01:23:32,173
- Why do they look so serious?
- All gathered by themselves.

1858
01:23:32,257 --> 01:23:33,383
They're all together.

1859
01:23:33,466 --> 01:23:35,010
I heard you guys were talking without me.

1860
01:23:35,969 --> 01:23:37,595
The great one has arrived.

1861
01:23:37,679 --> 01:23:39,305
- How was it?
- Huh?

1862
01:23:39,389 --> 01:23:42,142
I feel relieved right now.
I've totally made up my mind now.

1863
01:23:42,892 --> 01:23:44,894
- What's this?
- Like a weight's been lifted.

1864
01:23:44,978 --> 01:23:46,312
- I'm so jealous.
- I know.

1865
01:23:46,396 --> 01:23:48,815
What exactly went down?
None of us feel relieved at all.

1866
01:23:48,898 --> 01:23:51,192
- So you've made your decision?
- It's decided. I've made up my mind.

1867
01:23:51,276 --> 01:23:52,736
- Really?
- Oh…

1868
01:23:52,819 --> 01:23:54,529
- So who's your top pick now?
- Huh?

1869
01:23:54,612 --> 01:23:57,032
- Who's your top pick?
- Right now? It's Jeong-eun.

1870
01:23:57,741 --> 01:23:59,701
- Oh, it's changed.
- Ah, it's Jeong-eun now.

1871
01:23:59,784 --> 01:24:01,619
The only one that matters to me right now.

1872
01:24:01,703 --> 01:24:03,538
Wow, so you've really made up your mind.

1873
01:24:03,621 --> 01:24:04,998
You've made up your mind.

1874
01:24:05,999 --> 01:24:07,042
What about you?

1875
01:24:07,125 --> 01:24:12,005
Me? Well, I know the top
and second picks arrive in random order,

1876
01:24:12,088 --> 01:24:13,339
but Su-ji arrived first.

1877
01:24:13,423 --> 01:24:14,591
Ah, oh, okay.

1878
01:24:15,258 --> 01:24:16,593
As soon as she arrived today,

1879
01:24:16,676 --> 01:24:19,512
she mentioned
how she had received my letter,

1880
01:24:19,596 --> 01:24:22,766
and she also showed me
the gift I'd given her,

1881
01:24:22,849 --> 01:24:24,142
saying she would put it to good use,

1882
01:24:24,225 --> 01:24:27,562
so we agreed
we would continue to talk later.

1883
01:24:28,229 --> 01:24:30,106
Ah, another blow to Jin-woo.

1884
01:24:30,648 --> 01:24:32,692
It's so different
from what happened to Jin-woo.

1885
01:24:32,776 --> 01:24:34,486
But did you also bring that up?

1886
01:24:34,569 --> 01:24:37,906
How are you so sure about your top pick
that you don't have a second pick?

1887
01:24:37,989 --> 01:24:40,867
Uh, yeah. I just straight up
told her everything.

1888
01:24:41,910 --> 01:24:43,828
Ah, now Seung-hyun's the only one.

1889
01:24:43,912 --> 01:24:45,413
This must be painful for him.

1890
01:24:45,497 --> 01:24:48,708
"Ah, Jung-yun must be the one she likes."

1891
01:24:48,792 --> 01:24:51,544
I think her mind is more firmly made up
than you think too.

1892
01:24:53,004 --> 01:24:56,216
In my opinion, her mind
is much more firmly set on you,

1893
01:24:57,050 --> 01:24:58,218
more than you think.

1894
01:24:58,301 --> 01:24:59,761
So I'm rooting for you.

1895
01:24:59,844 --> 01:25:01,012
You got this.

1896
01:25:01,096 --> 01:25:03,556
- I'll try my best.
- You got this.

1897
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:05,892
- Let's all try our best.
- Mm-hmm.

1898
01:25:08,770 --> 01:25:10,563
I'm going straight for her, dude, I am.

1899
01:25:10,647 --> 01:25:12,148
That's the right thing to do.

1900
01:25:12,232 --> 01:25:14,025
If you didn't, that would be
like taking a detour

1901
01:25:14,109 --> 01:25:15,693
when your GPS is telling you where to go.

1902
01:25:15,777 --> 01:25:17,612
I'm going straight for it, bro. I mean it.

1903
01:25:17,695 --> 01:25:20,073
I won't feel bad
about doing this to you, bro.

1904
01:25:20,156 --> 01:25:22,325
Don't feel bad for me.

1905
01:25:22,408 --> 01:25:24,160
Keep that up,
and our team's gonna fall apart.

1906
01:25:24,244 --> 01:25:26,621
- I'm not gonna feel bad.
- You shouldn't.

1907
01:25:26,704 --> 01:25:28,498
All we need is for each of us
to play fair.

1908
01:25:28,581 --> 01:25:29,415
True.

1909
01:25:29,499 --> 01:25:32,502
- Good game.
- Oh, good game?

1910
01:25:32,585 --> 01:25:34,420
Does this end the race for Su-ji?

1911
01:25:34,504 --> 01:25:37,340
- It's over.
- It ended in just one day.

1912
01:25:37,423 --> 01:25:39,134
The Great Battle is over.

1913
01:25:39,217 --> 01:25:40,969
- The Su-ji Club is no more.
- No more.

1914
01:25:41,052 --> 01:25:44,848
All of them disbanded really quickly.
After being so hung up on her.

1915
01:25:44,931 --> 01:25:48,351
And with that, Yoon Jung-yun
has won the Su-ji tournament.

1916
01:25:48,434 --> 01:25:50,478
HAN SU-JI
AN JEONG-EUN

1917
01:25:50,562 --> 01:25:52,188
Su-ji's got a lot on her mind.

1918
01:25:52,981 --> 01:25:54,607
My heart is so heavy.

1919
01:25:55,275 --> 01:25:58,111
How exhausted must she be
after four dates?

1920
01:25:58,194 --> 01:26:01,865
She's been through so much
in such a short period of time too.

1921
01:26:04,075 --> 01:26:07,036
"I would like you to know…"

1922
01:26:08,955 --> 01:26:14,169
When I finally came back to the dorm
from the dates, I felt a little weird.

1923
01:26:14,252 --> 01:26:16,171
These guys were telling me they liked me,

1924
01:26:16,254 --> 01:26:19,215
so how could I completely
disregard their feelings

1925
01:26:19,299 --> 01:26:20,967
and think only about myself?

1926
01:26:21,551 --> 01:26:24,470
But since this is all
a new experience for me,

1927
01:26:24,554 --> 01:26:27,015
and these are feelings
I've never felt before,

1928
01:26:27,098 --> 01:26:29,517
I thought I should at least
try to talk to them.

1929
01:26:41,029 --> 01:26:44,782
I said I wanted to talk to them,
so I guess I should do that.

1930
01:26:46,409 --> 01:26:48,077
Let's get to it.

1931
01:26:48,661 --> 01:26:49,787
Let's talk.

1932
01:26:51,664 --> 01:26:53,249
Man, Su-ji's got such a cool personality.

1933
01:26:53,333 --> 01:26:55,710
She's going to them first,
even though she's the one being courted.

1934
01:26:55,793 --> 01:26:57,253
I know. Despite being so popular.

1935
01:26:57,337 --> 01:27:00,965
The guys shouldn't be settling things
between themselves like that.

1936
01:27:01,049 --> 01:27:02,675
They should be going outside to see her.

1937
01:27:09,807 --> 01:27:11,017
Is anyone here?

1938
01:27:15,980 --> 01:27:18,191
She seems
to be looking for people to talk to.

1939
01:27:18,274 --> 01:27:20,026
There's a strange vibe in the air.

1940
01:27:20,818 --> 01:27:22,654
Whoa, where did everyone go?

1941
01:27:42,715 --> 01:27:43,716
Hmm?

1942
01:27:49,013 --> 01:27:50,598
- Hello.
- Why are you alone?

1943
01:27:50,682 --> 01:27:52,225
- What did you say?
- Why are you alone?

1944
01:27:52,308 --> 01:27:53,476
Why am I alone?

1945
01:27:53,559 --> 01:27:55,144
I heard a rumor before coming here.

1946
01:27:55,228 --> 01:27:57,272
What rumor would that be?

1947
01:27:57,355 --> 01:28:00,024
You always look as if you've got
something important to say.

1948
01:28:00,108 --> 01:28:03,194
- I heard you were the star of the day.
- What is it? Huh?

1949
01:28:03,278 --> 01:28:05,530
You were the star of the day yesterday.

1950
01:28:05,613 --> 01:28:07,824
- Why don't we superstars have a little…
- Look who's talking.

1951
01:28:07,907 --> 01:28:09,993
Oh, right. Why don't we superstars
have a little chat?

1952
01:28:10,076 --> 01:28:12,704
- Whoa, what's this?
- They've both been on four dates.

1953
01:28:12,787 --> 01:28:14,664
They're the prom king and queen.

1954
01:28:14,747 --> 01:28:16,249
How did things go today?

1955
01:28:16,332 --> 01:28:17,333
It somewhat…

1956
01:28:18,209 --> 01:28:20,086
helped me get a handle on things.

1957
01:28:20,169 --> 01:28:21,879
- Mm-hmm.
- Mmm, really?

1958
01:28:22,630 --> 01:28:23,756
How about your day?

1959
01:28:24,799 --> 01:28:28,720
For me, things have gotten a little
complicated over the past two days.

1960
01:28:29,387 --> 01:28:30,596
Really? Why is that?

1961
01:28:33,224 --> 01:28:36,185
Well, my attraction to my top pick
has actually taken a hit.

1962
01:28:37,061 --> 01:28:38,062
Why's that?

1963
01:28:39,188 --> 01:28:43,776
Because everyone thinks your top pick
holds a very special place in your heart.

1964
01:28:44,527 --> 01:28:46,863
Do you think you've gone on too many dates
with the same person?

1965
01:28:46,946 --> 01:28:48,156
No, that's not the problem.

1966
01:28:48,239 --> 01:28:49,449
Mm-hmm.

1967
01:28:49,532 --> 01:28:53,286
It's just that our hobbies
and stuff like that,

1968
01:28:53,369 --> 01:28:56,497
they simply don't match as much as I…

1969
01:28:58,041 --> 01:29:02,086
Yeah, I'm starting to think
it might cause problems down the line.

1970
01:29:02,170 --> 01:29:03,629
Hobbies?

1971
01:29:03,713 --> 01:29:05,214
Well, for example…

1972
01:29:06,507 --> 01:29:11,220
Like, going to sing, or going hiking,
you know, stuff like that.

1973
01:29:11,304 --> 01:29:14,849
It's that I just want to do a lot of
different things with the person I like,

1974
01:29:14,932 --> 01:29:17,060
with the person I'm attracted to.

1975
01:29:17,727 --> 01:29:18,811
I'm that kind of person.

1976
01:29:18,895 --> 01:29:22,023
So if the other party isn't willing
to budge on those issues,

1977
01:29:22,648 --> 01:29:24,484
I'm worried that we might be incompatible

1978
01:29:24,567 --> 01:29:27,070
and have a rough time going forward.
That's why.

1979
01:29:27,695 --> 01:29:29,405
I think this is just the beginning for me.

1980
01:29:30,323 --> 01:29:31,616
What?

1981
01:29:31,699 --> 01:29:33,993
- You sure are a slow starter.
- I, um… I think so.

1982
01:29:36,746 --> 01:29:39,916
Well, I'm also taking things really slow,

1983
01:29:39,999 --> 01:29:42,794
so I feel like everything's
still a work in progress for me.

1984
01:29:42,877 --> 01:29:45,338
I'm just going to take things
at my own pace.

1985
01:29:46,130 --> 01:29:47,340
- What?
- Huh?

1986
01:29:48,007 --> 01:29:49,092
Ah…

1987
01:29:50,259 --> 01:29:51,844
Let's not push ourselves too hard.

1988
01:29:51,928 --> 01:29:54,597
It's okay to take your time
making a decision.

1989
01:29:57,475 --> 01:29:58,559
What is it?

1990
01:30:00,103 --> 01:30:01,729
I feel like you and I
are on the same page.

1991
01:30:01,813 --> 01:30:04,816
Oh, really? Wow, we sure do think alike.

1992
01:30:04,899 --> 01:30:07,110
- Really?
- Man, that…

1993
01:30:07,777 --> 01:30:09,946
- Hyuk-joon?
- I meant Su-ji.

1994
01:30:10,029 --> 01:30:11,155
You've got to be kidding me.

1995
01:30:11,239 --> 01:30:12,407
- Really?
- The vibes…

1996
01:30:12,490 --> 01:30:14,617
Oh, I'm also getting weird vibes
from these two right now.

1997
01:30:14,700 --> 01:30:16,828
Your clothes are about
to get torn to shreds.

1998
01:30:16,911 --> 01:30:17,787
Totally.

1999
01:30:18,538 --> 01:30:19,914
Yay, it's chicken.

2000
01:30:19,997 --> 01:30:22,083
- Hello.
- Ooh, chicken.

2001
01:30:22,166 --> 01:30:24,627
- Wow.
- What kind of chicken is it?

2002
01:30:24,710 --> 01:30:26,337
- Chicken nuggets.
- Ooh.

2003
01:30:26,421 --> 01:30:27,672
It looks so good.

2004
01:30:27,755 --> 01:30:29,006
Thank you for the meal.

2005
01:30:29,090 --> 01:30:31,467
Thank you, thank you for the meal.

2006
01:30:33,594 --> 01:30:35,388
God, that looks delicious.

2007
01:30:36,013 --> 01:30:37,765
Look at her with the gloves, digging in.

2008
01:30:37,849 --> 01:30:38,808
It's delicious.

2009
01:30:39,517 --> 01:30:41,644
You're a baby.

2010
01:30:41,727 --> 01:30:43,688
- What's this, now?
- What is it now?

2011
01:30:44,939 --> 01:30:46,774
TONIGHT, SPARKS HOUSE WILL OPEN

2012
01:30:46,858 --> 01:30:49,527
- Oh, so it's opening again.
- Sparks House?

2013
01:30:50,862 --> 01:30:53,030
THE SINGLES WHO WENT
ON THE MOST THREE-WAY DATES

2014
01:30:53,114 --> 01:30:53,948
WILL GO TO SPARKS HOUSE

2015
01:30:54,031 --> 01:30:55,741
WITH AN OPPOSITE-SEX PARTNER
OF THEIR CHOICE

2016
01:30:55,825 --> 01:30:57,869
CHOI HYUK-JOON - 4 DATES
MOST AMONG MEN

2017
01:30:57,952 --> 01:31:00,496
That would mean Hyuk-joon
and Su-ji will be going together.

2018
01:31:00,580 --> 01:31:01,706
SU-JI - 4 DATES
MOST AMONG WOMEN

2019
01:31:01,789 --> 01:31:03,332
Wow!

2020
01:31:03,875 --> 01:31:06,043
HYUK-JOON AND SU-JI,
SEND US THE NAME OF A PERSON…

2021
01:31:06,127 --> 01:31:07,462
No way.

2022
01:31:07,545 --> 01:31:10,840
…OF THE OPPOSITE SEX YOU'D LIKE
TO GO TO SPARKS HOUSE WITH

2023
01:31:10,923 --> 01:31:12,758
Oh, looks like some people
will be lonely tonight.

2024
01:31:12,842 --> 01:31:14,469
Wow.

2025
01:31:14,552 --> 01:31:16,596
- So they get to choose?
- That right there is a major perk.

2026
01:31:16,679 --> 01:31:19,182
What if Hyun-seo doesn't get to go
to Sparks House this time?

2027
01:31:19,265 --> 01:31:20,933
Oh, then who would he pick instead of…

2028
01:31:21,017 --> 01:31:22,268
Hyun-seo? Hold on.

2029
01:31:22,351 --> 01:31:23,853
Oh, God, I can't watch.

2030
01:31:24,729 --> 01:31:27,398
Ah, I was just really conflicted.

2031
01:31:27,940 --> 01:31:31,569
I felt like I was standing at a crossroads
where I had to choose a path.

2032
01:31:31,652 --> 01:31:34,572
So honestly, I feel like
my head's about to explode.

2033
01:31:34,655 --> 01:31:36,157
I wanted to talk to him more

2034
01:31:36,240 --> 01:31:39,410
and create opportunities
to keep checking my feelings,

2035
01:31:39,494 --> 01:31:41,370
so I was like, "Oh, this is great."

2036
01:31:43,831 --> 01:31:46,042
I feel like the next chapter
is going to open…

2037
01:31:46,125 --> 01:31:47,543
Think we'll start outside…

2038
01:31:47,627 --> 01:31:48,794
Mm-hmm, exactly.

2039
01:31:49,795 --> 01:31:51,130
SU-JI HAS MADE HER DECISION

2040
01:31:51,214 --> 01:31:53,090
Oh, those two are going to…

2041
01:31:53,174 --> 01:31:55,468
- Su-ji's picked Jung-yun.
- That was quick.

2042
01:31:55,551 --> 01:31:56,802
She made her choice in one minute.

2043
01:31:56,886 --> 01:32:00,723
Oh, Su-ji's picked Jung-yun.
That's a winner smile if I ever saw one.

2044
01:32:03,392 --> 01:32:07,230
I already had a feeling
that Su-ji had settled on Jung-yun.

2045
01:32:07,313 --> 01:32:10,066
But in all honesty,
it still hurt a little.

2046
01:32:10,149 --> 01:32:12,610
Even though I tried to be careful
not to show it too much.

2047
01:32:24,622 --> 01:32:26,249
He seems conflicted.

2048
01:32:29,669 --> 01:32:31,295
I really thought about it a lot.

2049
01:32:31,379 --> 01:32:33,631
To be honest,
everyone has their charm, after all.

2050
01:32:34,340 --> 01:32:35,550
Did you send it?

2051
01:32:36,634 --> 01:32:38,427
I mean, you should still go with Hyun-seo.

2052
01:32:38,511 --> 01:32:39,804
If Su-ji is in Hyuk-joon's heart,

2053
01:32:39,887 --> 01:32:41,973
that would make him even more averse
to bringing Hyun-seo.

2054
01:32:42,056 --> 01:32:44,433
I know. Is he going to choose
Han-ju instead?

2055
01:32:44,517 --> 01:32:45,810
Ask the outside world.

2056
01:32:45,893 --> 01:32:48,854
Exactly, can't we see it?
I'm so curious, seriously. I'm so…

2057
01:32:48,938 --> 01:32:51,566
But if things change now,
it can't be helped.

2058
01:32:52,567 --> 01:32:53,943
We've already gotten the big reveal.

2059
01:32:54,026 --> 01:32:55,903
- Where is he off to?
- All of a sudden?

2060
01:33:00,283 --> 01:33:01,993
What is he doing all of a sudden?

2061
01:33:02,660 --> 01:33:03,744
I guess he can't do it here.

2062
01:33:04,412 --> 01:33:06,080
Oh, God, what do I do?

2063
01:33:08,833 --> 01:33:10,751
Oh, I don't think Hyun-seo will get to go.

2064
01:33:10,835 --> 01:33:12,003
Maybe he won't choose anyone.

2065
01:33:12,086 --> 01:33:14,130
- What will it be?
- He's going to pick Han-ju.

2066
01:33:14,213 --> 01:33:15,673
Han-ju. I think he'll pick Han-ju.

2067
01:33:19,969 --> 01:33:22,054
I was supposed to send my answer by 7:00

2068
01:33:22,138 --> 01:33:23,639
after receiving that text,

2069
01:33:23,723 --> 01:33:27,685
but I must have sent it about…
40 minutes late.

2070
01:33:29,478 --> 01:33:32,064
CHOI HYUK-JOON HAS MADE HIS DECISION

2071
01:33:32,148 --> 01:33:33,274
He sent it.

2072
01:33:34,984 --> 01:33:36,694
Have you sent it yet or not?

2073
01:33:36,777 --> 01:33:38,529
- I just sent it.
- Oh, it's done?

2074
01:33:41,699 --> 01:33:43,659
- Shouldn't you get going?
- Huh? Oh, this is bad.

2075
01:33:44,994 --> 01:33:45,995
Oh, crap.

2076
01:33:46,746 --> 01:33:48,831
- What? What?
- Huh?

2077
01:33:48,914 --> 01:33:50,916
- What's this?
- Wow.

2078
01:33:51,500 --> 01:33:54,045
- Hold on, what is this?
- This is how they reveal this?

2079
01:33:54,128 --> 01:33:56,756
- What is it?
- Whose is this? It's not yours. Is it?

2080
01:33:56,839 --> 01:33:57,882
Huh?

2081
01:33:57,965 --> 01:33:59,383
- Huh, what's this?
- Wait, hold on. Wait…

2082
01:33:59,467 --> 01:34:00,551
Hold on.

2083
01:34:02,136 --> 01:34:04,680
- Who picked whom?
- Oh, my God. I can't watch!

2084
01:34:05,306 --> 01:34:07,266
He didn't pick anyone, did he?

2085
01:34:07,350 --> 01:34:09,518
- Won't we know who picked whom?
- Whoa, what?

2086
01:34:09,602 --> 01:34:11,103
Whoa, what?

2087
01:34:16,275 --> 01:34:18,194
- Huh? What is this?
- What?

2088
01:34:18,277 --> 01:34:21,614
CHOI HYUK-JOON
HAS CHOSEN AN JEONG-EUN

2089
01:34:21,697 --> 01:34:24,742
- Is this for real? Hold on.
- I know.

2090
01:34:25,618 --> 01:34:27,036
- I guess.
- Yeah.

2091
01:34:32,375 --> 01:34:33,376
Oh, boy.

2092
01:34:36,671 --> 01:34:39,173
Do whatever you want.
Do whatever you please.

2093
01:34:39,256 --> 01:34:41,801
She wasn't there for his dates
with his top two picks, though.

2094
01:34:41,884 --> 01:34:44,595
Can I… Can I just… Can I just go home?

2095
01:34:44,679 --> 01:34:46,430
- I feel the same way.
- I can't watch this now.

2096
01:34:46,514 --> 01:34:49,767
What do I do? Hyun-seo, my girl.
What do I do?

2097
01:34:49,850 --> 01:34:51,894
Should I have gone over this
with you in advance?

2098
01:34:51,977 --> 01:34:53,270
Oh, my God.

2099
01:34:54,063 --> 01:34:55,439
What even is this?

2100
01:34:56,607 --> 01:34:59,151
What the heck? It looks like she…
It must be a typo.

2101
01:34:59,235 --> 01:35:00,194
I know, right?

2102
01:35:00,277 --> 01:35:02,530
- She said it's a typo.
- So it's not Jung-yun?

2103
01:35:02,613 --> 01:35:03,948
Did she pick Seung-hyun?

2104
01:35:05,157 --> 01:35:07,243
HAN SU-JI
HAS CHOSEN CHOI HYUK-JOON

2105
01:35:08,160 --> 01:35:09,161
Huh?

2106
01:35:11,414 --> 01:35:13,958
- What did I tell you?
- I knew this would happen.

2107
01:35:15,584 --> 01:35:18,087
See that? I knew there was something off
about those two.

2108
01:35:18,170 --> 01:35:19,547
I kept getting goose bumps.

2109
01:35:19,630 --> 01:35:21,424
Wow, I'm seriously shaken
right now, no joke.

2110
01:35:21,507 --> 01:35:23,092
Man, I seriously got goose bumps.

2111
01:35:28,639 --> 01:35:32,768
I didn't like how everyone simply assumed
that there was no other possibility

2112
01:35:32,852 --> 01:35:35,980
and I would obviously
choose to go with Jung-yun.

2113
01:35:37,022 --> 01:35:38,899
I'm sure it'll come as a shock to them,

2114
01:35:38,983 --> 01:35:40,735
but they're free to judge as they wish.

2115
01:35:40,818 --> 01:35:42,528
I'm going to do what I want.

2116
01:35:44,029 --> 01:35:45,614
She should have been honest with me.

2117
01:35:45,698 --> 01:35:48,743
Instead, it's like she's toying
with my emotions.

2118
01:35:48,826 --> 01:35:51,203
I'm telling you. It was a total betrayal.

2119
01:35:51,287 --> 01:35:52,872
From my point of view, I was played.

2120
01:35:52,955 --> 01:35:54,957
But if I get Hyuk-joon again,

2121
01:35:55,583 --> 01:35:57,752
I think it'll be really hard for me.
